{"title_page": "Total DramaRama", "text_new": "{{About|the spin-off|the original series|Total Drama}}\n\n{{short description|American/Canadian animated comedy series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Total DramaRama\n| image                    = File:Total DramaRama.png\n| size                     = \n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = [[Animated]]<br />[[Comedy]]<br />[[Surreal comedy]]\n| creator                  = [[Tom McGillis]]<br />[[Jennifer Pertsch]]\n| director                 = Chad Hicks<br />Keith Oliver<br />Christos Katopodis<br />George Elliott\n| based_on                 = \n| voices                   = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Deven Mack]]\n* [[Emilie-Claire Barlow]]\n* [[Katie Crown]]\n* [[Cory Doran]]\n* [[Scott McCord]]\n* [[Drew Nelson (actor)|Drew Nelson]]\n* [[Sarah Gadon]]\n* [[Christian Potenza]]\n* [[Kristin Fairlie]]\n* Lilly Bartlam\n* Bahia Watson\n* [[Darren Frost]]\n* Wyatt White\n* Evany Rosen\n}}\n| theme_music_composer     = [[Voodoo Highway Music & Post Inc.]]\n| opentheme                = \n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = [[Voodoo Highway Music & Post Inc.]]\n| country                  = Canada<br />United States\n| language                 = English<br />French\n| num_seasons              = 2<!-- increment when new season begins -->\n| num_episodes             = 59<!-- increment when new episode airs -->\n| executive_producer       = [[Jennifer Pertsch]]<br />[[Tom McGillis]]<br /> George Eliott <br />[[Brian Irving]]\n| company                  = [[Fresh TV|Fresh TV Inc.]]<br>[[Corus Entertainment]]\n| distributor              = [[Cake Entertainment]]\n| picture_format           = [[HDTV]] [[1080p]]\n| runtime                  = 11 minutes\n| network                  = [[Teletoon]] (Canada)<br />[[Cartoon Network]] (US)\n| first_run                = \n| first_aired              = {{start date|2018|9|1}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| website                  = \n| production_website       = \n| preceded_by              = ''[[Total Drama]]''\n| related                  = ''[[Total Drama Presents: The Ridonculous Race|The Ridonculous Race]]''<br />''[[6teen]]''\n}}\n\n'''''Total DramaRama''''' (originally titled '''''Total Daycare Drama''''' or '''''Total Drama Daycare''''') is a Canadian [[animated]] [[comedy]] series. It is a [[Fictional crossover|crossover]] [[Prequel|prequel]] [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] set in an alternate universe of ''[[Total Drama]]'' and ''[[6teen]]'' and is the 2nd spin-off of ''[[Total Drama]]'', after ''[[Total Drama Presents: The Ridonculous Race|The Ridonculous Race]]''. Created by [[Tom McGillis]] and [[Jennifer Pertsch]], the series is produced by [[Fresh TV|Fresh TV Inc.]] in association with [[Corus Entertainment]] and [[Cartoon Network]], and distributed by [[Cake Entertainment]]. It premiered on [[Cartoon Network]] in the United States on September 1, 2018, on [[Teletoon]] in Canada on October 7, 2018, on [[Pop (UK and Ireland)|POP]] in the United Kingdom on 3 June 2019 and on [[K2 (TV channel)|K2]] in Italy on 8 April 2019. \n\nThe series premiered in France on [[Canal+ Family]] and on [[T\u00e9l\u00e9toon+]] on 4 November 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tv-programme.com/defis-extremes-retour-a-la-maternelle_serie/|title=D\u00e9fis extr\u00eames : retour \u00e0 la maternelle (S\u00e9rie) \u2022 Programme TV & Replay|last=|first=|date=|website=tv-programme.com|language=fr|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=}}</ref> On February 13, 2019, the series was green lit for a second season, which premiered in the United States on January 11, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kidscreen.com/2019/02/13/cake-fresh-tv-get-more-dramarama/|title=CAKE, Fresh TV get more Dramarama|work=Kidscreen|date=February 13, 2019|access-date=March 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Premise ==\nThe series re-introduces some of the original \"Total Drama\" characters who are entered into an alternate universe where they are aged down from teenagers to toddlers, being taken care of by Chef Hatchet. Each episode features dream sequences, cutaways, visual jokes, confessionals, and flashbacks.<ref name=\"daycare\">{{cite web|url=http://kidscreen.com/2017/12/19/cn-teletoon-open-up-total-drama-daycare/|title=CN, Teletoon open up ''Total Drama Daycare''|work=Kidscreen|date=December 19, 2017|access-date=December 19, 2017}}</ref> A ''Ridonculous Race'' contestant, MacArthur, has made recurring appearances and several other characters from the ''[[Total Drama]]'' series and ''The Ridonculous Race'' have made cameo appearances throughout the series.\n\n==Voice cast==\n*[[Deven Mack]] as Chef Hatchet\n*[[Emilie-Claire Barlow]] as Courtney\n*Lilly Bartlam as Gwen\n*[[Katie Crown]] as Izzy\n*[[Cory Doran]] as Noah\n*[[Kristin Fairlie]] as Bridgette\n*[[Darren Frost]] as Harold\n*[[Sarah Gadon]] as Beth\n*[[Scott McCord]] as Owen\n*[[Drew Nelson (actor)|Drew Nelson]] as Duncan\n*[[Christian Potenza]] as Jude Lizowski (from ''[[6teen]]'')\n*Bahia Watson as Leshawna\n*Wyatt White as Cody\n*Evany Rosen as MacArthur (from ''[[Total Drama Presents: The Ridonculous Race|The Ridonculous Race]]'')\n\nIn addition, notable characters and voice actors have cameoed in the series:\n\nSeason 1:\n* Nikki, another character from ''6teen'' has made a non-speaking cameo in \"Duck Duck Juice\". \n* [[Megan Fahlenbock]] reprises her role as Gwen in \"Tiger Fail\". \n* [[Terry McGurrin]] also reprises his role as Don, the host of ''The Ridonculous Race'', who is working as a scientist in \"Know it All\".\n* Geoff makes a very brief cameo in a slot machine in \"Stay Goth, Poodle Girl, Stay Goth\"\n* Heather, Topher, and Shawn make a cameo in the episode \"Gum and Gummer\".\n* Devin, Trent, and Chet make a brief cameo in Harold's comic in \"Invasion Of The Booger Snatchers\".\n* Rodney and Heather make a cameo at the beach in \"Duncan Disorderly\".\n\nSeason 2:\n* [[Dwayne Hill]] reprises his role as Josh in \"The Tooth About Zombies.\"\n* Don makes a non-speaking cameo in \"Exercising the Demons\"\n\n==Production==\nThe show was under production as of December 19, 2017.<ref name=\"daycare\" /><ref name=\"daycare 2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/tv/pint-sized-prequel-total-drama-daycare-announced/ |title=Pint-Sized Prequel 'Total Daycare Drama' Announced |work=Animation Magazine |date=December 19, 2017 |access-date=August 25, 2018}}</ref> It first aired in the U.S. on Cartoon Network on September 1, 2018.<ref name=\"dramaRama\">{{cite web|url=http://kidscreen.com/2018/06/04/corus-unveils-201819-kids-programming-slate/|title=Corus unveils 2018/19 kids programming slate|work=Kidscreen|date=June 4, 2018|access-date=June 4, 2018}}</ref> Jennifer Pertsch revealed in an interview with TV Kids that Fresh took \"11 favorites from the original cast and aged them down to 4\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://issuu.com/worldscreen/docs/tv_kids_miptv_2018/68|title=TV Kids MIPTV 2018|publisher=|accessdate=19 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nIt was originally titled ''Total Daycare Drama'' as confirmed by Christine Thompson as well as ads by Cartoon Network. It was later titled ''Total Drama Daycare'' before becoming known as ''Total DramaRama'', a reference to the audition tape from  generation two contestant, Anne Maria.<ref name=\"dramaRama\" />\n\n== Episodes ==\n\n=== Series overview ===\n{{Series overview\n\n| color1    = #7EC0EE\n| link1     = #Season 1 (2018-19)\n| episodes1 = 51\n| start1    = {{Start date|2018|9|1}}\n| end1      = {{End date|2019|11|30}}\n\n| color2    = #8219C3\n| link2     = #Season 2 (2020)\n| episodes2 = \n| start2    = {{Start date|2020|1|11}}\n| end2      = \n}}\n\n===Season 1 (2018-19)===\n{{Episode table\n|background  = #7EC0EE\n|overall     = \n|season      = \n|title       = \n|titleR      = <ref name=\"The Futon Critic\" /><ref name=\"Zap2it Season 1\" />\n|writer      = \n|airdate     = \n|airdateT    = Canadian air date\n|altdate     = \n|altdate