via|Latvia]]\n|712\n|5\n|88\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://twitter.com/SPKCentrs |title=SPKC.gov.lv (@SPKCentrs) |last=SPKC.gov.lvVerified account |publisher=Twitter |access-date=2020-04-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203140211/https://twitter.com/SPKCentrs |archive-date=3 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|AND}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Andorra|Andorra]]\n|704\n|35\n|205\n|\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|ALB}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Albania|Albania]]\n|548\n|26\n|302\n|\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|KOS}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Kosovo|Kosovo]]\n|510\n|12\n|93\n|<ref>{{citation |title=2020 coronavirus pandemic in Kosovo |date=2020-03-25 |url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Kosovo&oldid=947299455 |work=Wikipedia |language=en |access-date=2020-03-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200406000620/https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Kosovo&oldid=947299455 |archive-date=6 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|SMR}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in San Marino|San Marino]]\n|455\n|39\n|60\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iss.sm/on-line/home/articolo49014186.html |title=Gruppo coordinamento emergenze \u2013 aggiornamento 27 marzo |date=2020-03-27 |website=Istituto per la Sicurezza Sociale |language=it |access-date=2020-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327134149/http://www.iss.sm/on-line/home/articolo49014186.html |archive-date=27 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Malta}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Malta|Malta]]\n|427\n|3\n|118\n|\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|MNE}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Montenegro|Montenegro]]\n|307\n|5\n|55\n|\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Isle of Man}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Isle of Man|Isle of Man]]\n|297\n|6\n|180\n|\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|JEY}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Jersey|Jersey]]\n|245\n|12\n|\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gov.je:80/Health/Coronavirus/Pages/CoronavirusCases.aspx|title=Coronavirus (COVID-19) cases|last=Jersey|first=States of|website=www.gov.je|language=en|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Bailiwick of Guernsey}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Guernsey|Guernsey]]\n|239\n|9\n|87\n|<ref>{cite web |author1=Public Health Services |title=COVID-19 Coronavirus \u2013 Testing results |url=https://www.gov.gg/covid19testresults |website=www.gov.gg |accessdate=16 April 2020 |location=St Peter Port |language=en |date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|FRO}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Faroe Islands|Faroe Islands]]\n|184\n|0\n|171\n|\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|GIB}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Gibraltar|Gibraltar]]\n|132\n|0\n|105\n|\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Monaco}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Monaco|Monaco]]\n|94\n|3\n|20\n|\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|LIE}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Liechtenstein|Liechtenstein]]\n|79\n|1\n|55\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.volksblatt.li/default.aspx |title=Aktuelle Nachrichten aus Liechtenstein \u2013 volksblatt.li |website=Liechtensteiner Volksblatt |language=de-DE |access-date=11 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200217222906/https://www.volksblatt.li/default.aspx |archive-date=17 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Donetsk People's Republic}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Donetsk People's Republic|Donetsk PR]]\n|32\n|0\n|2\n|\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Luhansk People's Republic}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Luhansk People's Republic|Luhansk PR]]\n|17\n|0\n|1\n|\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|VAT}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Vatican City|Vatican City]]\n|8\n|0\n|2\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vaticannews.va/en/vatican-city/news/2020-03/coronavirus-pope-positive-vatican-santa-marta-holy-see.html |title=Covid-19: 2 new cases in the Vatican, another 170 people tested \u2013 Vatican News |date=2020-03-26 |publisher=Vaticannews.va |access-date=2020-03-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328205016/https://www.vaticannews.va/en/vatican-city/news/2020-03/coronavirus-pope-positive-vatican-santa-marta-holy-see.html |archive-date=28 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n|'''Total'''\n|'''1,143,786'''\n|'''101,804'''\n|'''304,630'''\n|\n|}\n\n== Pandemic by country and territory ==\nCounting of cases are subject to the number of tested people.\n\n=== Albania ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Albania|files=0}}\n\n=== Andorra ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Andorra}}\n\n=== Austria ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Austria|files=0}}\n\n=== Belarus ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Belarus|files=0}}\n\n=== Belgium ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Belgium}}\n\n===Bosnia and Herzegovina===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Bosnia and Herzegovina}}\n\n=== Bulgaria ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Bulgaria}}\n\n=== Croatia ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Croatia}}\nOn 25 February, [[Croatia]] confirmed its first case, a 26-year-old man who had been in [[Milan]], [[Italy]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2020/feb/25/coronavirus-live-updates-outbreak-latest-news-italy-italia-deaths-symptoms-china-stocks-wall-street-dow-jones-economy-falls?page=with:block-5e550d8a8f086a28115b222d#block-5e550d8a8f086a28115b222d |title=Croatia latest European country to confirm coronavirus case |date=25 February 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=25 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226140456/https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2020/feb/25/coronavirus-live-updates-outbreak-latest-news-italy-italia-deaths-symptoms-china-stocks-wall-street-dow-jones-economy-falls?page=with:block-5e550d8a8f086a28115b222d#block-5e550d8a8f086a28115b222d |archive-date=26 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 26 February, two new cases were confirmed, one being the twin brother of the first.<ref name=\"hr.n1info.com\">{{cite web |url=http://hr.n1info.com/English/NEWS/a486123/Croatia-confirms-third-case-of-coronavirus-infection.html |title=Croatia confirms third case of coronavirus infection |website=N1 HR |language=hr |access-date=26 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226181744/http://hr.n1info.com/English/NEWS/a486123/Croatia-confirms-third-case-of-coronavirus-infection.html |archive-date=26 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> In March 2020, a cluster of cases were reported in numerous Croatian cities. On 12 March, the first recovery was reported, and on 18 March the first death from the virus was confirmed. On 19 March, the number of recorded cases surpassed 100. On 21 March, it surpassed 200. On 25 March, it surpassed 400. On 31 March, it surpassed 800. The pandemic in Croatia occurred during the [[Presidency of the Council of the European Union|Croatian Presidency]] of the [[Council of the European Union]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/policies/covid-19-coronavirus-outbreak/ |title=COVID-19 coronavirus outbreak |website=consilium.europa.eu |access-date=31 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330103912/https://www.consilium.europa.eu/en/policies/covid-19-coronavirus-outbreak/ |archive-date=30 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, an [[2020 Zagreb earthquake|intense earthquake hit Zagreb]], the capital of Croatia, causing problems in enforcement of [[social distancing]] measures set out by the [[Government of Croatia|Government]]. The earthquake could also be felt across much of Croatia, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Hungary, Slovenia, and Austria.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.jutarnji.hr/vijesti/hrvatska/snazni-potresi-uzdrmali-zagreb-prvo-podrhtavanje-zabiljezeno-u-624-drugo-pola-sata-kasnije-gradani-na-ulicama-stete-ogromne-poginula-curica-15/10120042/ |title=SNA\u017dNI POTRESI UZDRMALI ZAGREB Prvo podrhtavanje zabilje\u017eeno u 6.24, drugo pola sata kasnije, gra\u0111ani na ulicama, \u0161tete ogromne, poginula curica (15) |website=Jutarnji List |access-date=22 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322082628/https://www.jutarnji.hr/vijesti/hrvatska/snazni-potresi-uzdrmali-zagreb-prvo-podrhtavanje-zabiljezeno-u-624-drugo-pola-sata-kasnije-gradani-na-ulicama-stete-ogromne-poginula-curica-15/10120042/ |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.timeout.com/croatia/news/large-earthquake-hits-zagreb-032220 |title=Large earthquake hits Zagreb |website=timeout.com |access-date=22 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322084509/https://www.timeout.com/croatia/news/large-earthquake-hits-zagreb-032220 |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAccording to [[Oxford University]], as of 24 March, Croatia is the country with the world's strictest restrictions and measures for infection reduction in relation to the number of infected.<ref>{{cite news |last=Veljkovi\u0107 |first=Sandra |url=https://m.vecernji.hr/vijesti/oxford-hrvatska-ima-najstroze-mjere-u-europi-iza-su-samo-srbija-i-sirija-1389281 |title=Oxford: Hrvatska ima najstro\u017ee mjere u Europi. Bero\u0161: Pa\u017eljivo balansiramo |date=26 March 2020 |work=Ve\u010dernji list |url-status=live |language=Croatian |access-date=30 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329150316/https://m.vecernji.hr/vijesti/oxford-hrvatska-ima-najstroze-mjere-u-europi-iza-su-samo-srbija-i-sirija-1389281 |archive-date=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe government set up a website for all information about the virus and a new phone line 113 that has volunteers answering questions.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rtl.hr/vijesti-hr/koronavirus/3665535/hrvatska-ima-12-novih-bolesnika-81-zarazenih-ukupno-situacija-u-europi-nije-dobra/ |title=Koronavirusom zara\u017eena 81 osoba! Za gra\u0111ane otvorena linija 113, u kr\u0161enju izolacije uhva\u0107ene 132 osobe |last=N.C. |date=18 March 2020 |website=rtl.hr |language=hr |url-status=live |access-date=19 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319210451/https://www.rtl.hr/vijesti-hr/koronavirus/3665535/hrvatska-ima-12-novih-bolesnika-81-zarazenih-ukupno-situacija-u-europi-nije-dobra/ |archive-date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Cyprus ===\n<!-- \nPlease also edit [[2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Asia#Cyprus]] to make the information the same\nAlso, do not remove the Northern Cyprus link, the Cyprus article doesn't talk about cases in Northern Cyprus!\n -->\n{{Main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Cyprus|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Northern Cyprus|l2=Northern Cyprus}}\nOn 9 March, [[Cyprus]] confirmed its first two cases, one in Nicosia and one in Limassol.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/AFP/status/1237044503464288261 |title=#BREAKING Cyprus reports 2 coronavirus cases, all EU states now hitpic.twitter.com/FBQYaTdUbK |date=9 March 2020 |website=@AFP |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309160200/https://twitter.com/AFP/status/1237044503464288261 |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://cyprus-mail.com/2020/03/09/breaking-news-two-cases-of-coronavirus-confirmed/ |title=BREAKING NEWS: Two cases of coronavirus confirmed |date=9 March 2020 |via=cyprus-mail.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://daily-cyprus.com/2020/03/09/two-patients-have-tested-positive-for-the-coronavirus-in-cyprus/ |title=Two patients have tested positive for the coronavirus in Cyprus |work=Daily Cyprus News |url-status=live |access-date=3 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319211123/https://daily-cyprus.com/2020/03/09/two-patients-have-tested-positive-for-the-coronavirus-in-cyprus/ |archive-date=19 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Czech Republic ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Czech Republic}}\n[[File:Autobus, nevstupovat k \u0159idi\u010di (01).jpg|thumb|210px|It is forbidden to enter front section of buses of the [[Prague Integrated Transport|Prague Public Transport]] during the pandemic (14 March 2020)]]\nThe first case was reported in the country on 1 March.<ref name=\"CZE\" /> As of 22 March there had been 1120 confirmed cases, with one lethal outcome.<ref name=\"CZE\" />\n\nOn 12 March, the Czech Republic declared a 30-day state of emergency and barred entry to non-residents from China, South Korea, Iran, Italy, Spain, Austria, Germany, Switzerland, Sweden, UK, Norway, Denmark and France.<ref name=\"cnnTBs\">{{cite news |url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/coronavirus-travel-bans/index.html |title=Coronavirus: Which countries have travel bans? |date=17 March 2020 |access-date=17 March 2020 |website=cnn.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320091122/https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/coronavirus-travel-bans/index.html |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe Czech Republic banned people from going out in public without wearing a [[Surgical mask|face mask]] or covering their nose and mouth.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/30/czechs-get-to-work-making-masks-after-government-decree-coronavirus |title=Czechs get to work making masks after government decree |date=30 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=2 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330235911/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/30/czechs-get-to-work-making-masks-after-government-decree-coronavirus |archive-date=30 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Denmark ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Denmark}}\n{{for|Greenland|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Greenland}}\n{{for|Faroe Islands|2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Faroe Islands}}\nOn 27 February, Denmark confirmed its first case.<ref>{{cite news |last=Braagaard |first=Natali |url=https://nyheder.tv2.dk/samfund/2020-02-27-dansker-smittet-med-coronavirus |title=Dansker smittet med coronavirus |date=27 February 2020 |work=TV 2 |access-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live |language=da |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227054434/https://nyheder.tv2.dk/samfund/2020-02-27-dansker-smittet-med-coronavirus |archive-date=27 February 2020 }}</ref>\n\nAs of 16 March, there have been 898 confirmed cases in Denmark, including 11 in the Faroe Islands (see below).<ref name=\"STPS numbers\">{{Cite news |url=https://politi.dk/coronavirus-i-danmark/foelg-smittespredningen-globalt-regionalt-og-lokalt |title=F\u00f8lg smittespredningen globalt, regionalt og lokalt |date=16 March 2020 |work=Styrelsen for Patientsikkerhed ([[Ministry of Health (Denmark)|Ministry of Health]]) |access-date=16 March 2020 |url-status=live |language=da |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320214647/https://politi.dk/coronavirus-i-danmark/foelg-smittespredningen-globalt-regionalt-og-lokalt |archive-date=20 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\nNumerous preventive measures gradually were implemented. Starting on 13 March, schools, universities and similar places were closed, while most people in non-essential functions have been sent home to work.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Svendsen |first=Anders Byskov |url=https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/politik/corona-tiltag-elever-og-studerende-paa-alle-uddannelsesinstitutioner-sendes-hjem-nu |title=Corona-tiltag: Elever og studerende p\u00e5 alle uddannelsesinstitutioner sendes hjem nu |date=11 March 2020 |work=DR |access-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live |language=da |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311195948/https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/politik/corona-tiltag-elever-og-studerende-paa-alle-uddannelsesinstitutioner-sendes-hjem-nu |archive-date=11 March 2020 }}</ref> On 14 March, the borders were closed for all entries, except Danish citizens, people with a residence permit, people with an important reason for visiting, and transport of goods.<ref>{{Cite news |last=M\u00f8ller |first=Albert Schmidt |url=https://nyheder.tv2.dk/samfund/2020-03-13-statsministeren-lukker-graensen-for-at-bremse-coronavirussen |title=Statsministeren lukker gr\u00e6nsen for at bremse coronavirussen |date=13 March 2020 |work=TV 2 |access-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live |language=da |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314180452/https://nyheder.tv2.dk/samfund/2020-03-13-statsministeren-lukker-graensen-for-at-bremse-coronavirussen |archive-date=14 March 2020 }}</ref><ref name=cnnTBs/>\n\n=== Estonia ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Estonia}}\nOn 27 February [[Estonia]] confirmed its first case, an Iranian citizen, travelling from Iran via Turkey.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://news.err.ee/1057196/first-coronavirus-case-found-in-estonia |title=First Coronavirus case found in Estonia |access-date=27 February 2020 |publisher=[[Eesti Rahvusringh\u00e4\u00e4ling|ERR]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227065704/https://news.err.ee/1057196/first-coronavirus-case-found-in-estonia |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAs of 11 March there were 17 confirmed cases in Estonia. 12 of them had returned with the infection from Northern Italy, one from France, one from Iran and one from undisclosed risk area.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.err.ee/1060677/eestis-on-koroonaviirus-tuvastatud-kumnel-inimesel |title=Eestis on koroonaviirus tuvastatud k\u00fcmnel inimesel |date=6 March 2020 |publisher=ERR |language=et |trans-title=Ten people have been diagnosed with coronavirus in Estonia |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307152100/https://www.err.ee/1060677/eestis-on-koroonaviirus-tuvastatud-kumnel-inimesel |archive-date=7 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.err.ee/1061912/teisipaevase-seisuga-on-eestis-koroonaviirus-tuvastatud-13-inimesel |title=Teisip\u00e4evase seisuga on Eestis koroonaviirus tuvastatud 13 inimesel |date=10 March 2020 |publisher=ERR |language=Estonian |trans-title=As of Tuesday, 13 people have been diagnosed with coronavirus in Estonia |access-date=10 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311180618/https://www.err.ee/1061912/teisipaevase-seisuga-on-eestis-koroonaviirus-tuvastatud-13-inimesel |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> First two cases of virus transmitting locally were in [[Saaremaa]] after international volleyball competition involving a team from [[Milan]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://news.err.ee/1062392/three-new-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-confirmed-in-estonia |title=Three new cases of coronavirus disease confirmed in Estonia |date=11 March 2020 |publisher=ERR |access-date=12 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311204452/https://news.err.ee/1062392/three-new-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-confirmed-in-estonia |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nFrom 12 March the virus was spreading locally. The number of infected grew fast reaching 109 on 14 March.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://news.err.ee/1063959/109-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-confirmed-in-estonia |title=109 cases of coronavirus disease confirmed in Estonia |date=14 March 2020 |publisher=ERR |access-date=14 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315140308/https://news.err.ee/1063959/109-cases-of-coronavirus-disease-confirmed-in-estonia |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== Finland ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Finland}}\nThe first case was reported in the country on 28 January.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/osasto/news/finlands_first_coronavirus_case_confirmed_in_lapland/11182855|title=Finland's first coronavirus case confirmed in Lapland|website=Yle Uutiset}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.helsinkitimes.fi/finland/finland-news/domestic/17272-finland-s-first-coronavirus-patient-began-to-show-symptoms-three-days-ago.html |title=Finland's first coronavirus patient began to show symptoms three days ago |access-date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309215132/https://www.helsinkitimes.fi/finland/finland-news/domestic/17272-finland-s-first-coronavirus-patient-began-to-show-symptoms-three-days-ago.html |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== France ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in France}}\n[[File:Super U \u2013 des rayons vides.jpg|thumb|210px|Empty supermarket shelves in [[Annonay]], France, on 14 March 2020.]]\n\nOn 24 January, the first case in Europe was confirmed in [[Bordeaux]]. Two more cases were confirmed in [[Paris]] by the end of the day, all of them originated from China. A cluster of infections was discovered in Haute-Savoie which originated from a British national who had visited [[Singapore]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.20minutes.fr/bordeaux/2703783-20200126-coronavirus-sait-cas-detecte-bordeaux |title=Coronavirus : Que sait-on du cas d\u00e9tect\u00e9 \u00e0 Bordeaux ? |last=Provenzano |first=Elsa |date=26 January 2020 |website=20 Minutes |language=fr |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200219143036/https://www.20minutes.fr/bordeaux/2703783-20200126-coronavirus-sait-cas-detecte-bordeaux |archive-date=19 February 2020 |access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":12\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.lefigaro.fr/sciences/coronavirus-5-nouveaux-cas-en-france-20200208 |title=Coronavirus : 5 nouveaux cas confirm\u00e9s en France |last=Figaro |first=Le |date=8 February 2020 |website=Le Figaro.fr |language=fr |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200208101615/https://www.lefigaro.fr/sciences/coronavirus-5-nouveaux-cas-en-france-20200208 |archive-date=8 February 2020 |access-date=8 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\":22\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sante/virus/coronavirus/coronavirus-une-11e-guerison-en-france-plus-aucun-malade-hospitalise-6751169 |title=Coronavirus. Une 11e gu\u00e9rison en France, \" plus aucun malade hospitalis\u00e9 \" |date=24 February 2020 |website=Ouest-France.fr |language=fr |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224202543/https://www.ouest-france.fr/sante/virus/coronavirus/coronavirus-une-11e-guerison-en-france-plus-aucun-malade-hospitalise-6751169 |archive-date=24 February 2020 |access-date=24 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nFrom 31 January to 9 February, nearly 550 people were repatriated from [[Wuhan]] on a series of evacuation flights arriving at Creil Air Base in [[Oise]] and [[Istres-Le Tub\u00e9 Air Base]] in [[Istres]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.defense.gouv.fr/actualites/international/l-armee-de-l-air-au-service-des-francais |title=L'Arm\u00e9e de l'air au service des Fran\u00e7ais |date=2 February 2020 |website=defense.gouv.fr |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327233053/https://www.defense.gouv.fr/actualites/international/l-armee-de-l-air-au-service-des-francais |archive-date=27 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 14 February, an 80-year-old Chinese tourist died in [[Bichat\u2013Claude Bernard Hospital]], [[Paris]], marking the first death from COVID-19 in Europe and France.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51514837 |title=First coronavirus death confirmed in Europe |date=15 February 2020 |work=BBC News |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200219204410/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51514837 |archive-date=19 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAccording to regional council president Jean Rottner, the starting point for the first intense wave in Alsace was the Fasting Meeting of the Protestant Free Church of La Porte Ouverte in Mulhouse, with more than 2500 visitors, in mid-February.<ref name=\"faz\">{{Cite news |last=Wiegel |first=Michaela |url=https://www.faz.net/1.6702139 |title=Corona-Krise im Elsass: \"Wir sind unendlich dankbar f\u00fcr die Hilfe aus Deutschland\" |date=2020-03-30 |work=FAZ.NET |access-date=2020-03-30 |last2=Paris |language=de |issn=0174-4909}}</ref>\nOn 12 March, French president Emmanuel Macron announced on public television that all schools and all universities would close from Monday 16 March until further notice. The next day, the prime minister \u00c9douard Philippe banned gatherings of more than 100 people, not including public transportation. The following day, the prime minister ordered the closure of all nonessential public places, including restaurants, caf\u00e9s, cinemas, and discoth\u00e8ques, effective at midnight.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51892477 |title=Coronavirus: Spain and France announce sweeping restrictions |date=15 March 2020 |work=BBC News |access-date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320221934/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51892477 |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAs of 14 March, there had been 4,499 confirmed cases (a near-four-fold increase over the number 5 days previously), and 91 deaths in France.<ref>[https://www.santepubliquefrance.fr/maladies-et-traumatismes/maladies-et-infections-respiratoires/infection-a-coronavirus/articles/infection-au-nouveau-coronavirus-sars-cov-2-covid-19-france-et-monde Infection au nouveau Coronavirus (SARS-CoV-2), COVID-19, France et Monde] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321143945/https://www.santepubliquefrance.fr/maladies-et-traumatismes/maladies-et-infections-respiratoires/infection-a-coronavirus/articles/infection-au-nouveau-coronavirus-sars-cov-2-covid-19-france-et-monde |date=21 March 2020 }} ''www.santepubliquefrance.fr'', accessed 12 March 2020</ref>\n\nAs of 20 March, the number of confirmed cases had risen to 12,612, while the number of deaths reached 450.<ref name=\"coronacount\" />\nAs of March 30, more than six hundred doctors and other medical workers are suing the former Minister of Health and the Prime Minister for \"culpable negligence\" in failing to prepare for the epidemic.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Collins |first=Lauren |url=https://www.newyorker.com/science/medical-dispatch/here-the-terrorists-are-inside-the-french-psychiatrist-who-counsels-crisis-doctors |title=\"Here, the Terrorists Are Inside\": The French Psychiatrist Who Counsels Crisis Doctors |date=2020-03-30 |work=The New Yorker |access-date=2020-03-31 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200331155454/https://www.newyorker.com/science/medical-dispatch/here-the-terrorists-are-inside-the-french-psychiatrist-who-counsels-crisis-doctors |archive-date=31 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nUntil 1 April, the daily update of the number of deaths in France included only deaths in hospitals, with deaths in retirement homes or at home not included in the update.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.20minutes.fr/sante/2748183-20200325-coronavirus-nombre-deces-ephad-probablement-beaucoup-plus-lourd-bilan-officiel |title=En Ehpad, le nombre de morts du Covid-19 plus lourd que le bilan officiel |date=2020-03-25 |work=20 minutes |access-date=2020-03-30 |language=fr |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327111304/https://www.20minutes.fr/sante/2748183-20200325-coronavirus-nombre-deces-ephad-probablement-beaucoup-plus-lourd-bilan-officiel |archive-date=27 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Deaths in retirement homes were included in the reported figures from 2 April, causing totals to increase substantially.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200403-french-hospitals-record-deadliest-day-with-588-coronavirus-deaths|title=French hospitals record deadliest day with 588 coronavirus deaths|date=3 April 2020|publisher=France 24|accessdate=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Germany ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Germany}}\n\n=== Greece ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Greece}}\nOn 26 February, the first case in Greece was confirmed, a 38-year-old woman from [[Thessaloniki]] who had recently visited [[Northern Italy]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-greece-idUSKCN20K1IA |title=Greece confirms first coronavirus case |date=26 February 2020 |work=Reuters |access-date=26 February 2020 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226113222/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-greece-idUSKCN20K1IA |archive-date=26 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The next day, the first patient's 9-year-old child and another 40-year-old woman, who had travelled to Italy, also tested positive.<ref name=\":172\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-deytero-thetiko-kroysma-stin-ellada-paidi-38hronis |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u0394\u03b5\u03cd\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03bf \u03b8\u03b5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 -\u03a4\u03bf \u03c0\u03b1\u03b9\u03b4\u03af \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 38\u03c7\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b7\u03c2 {{!}} \u0395\u039b\u039b\u0391\u0394\u0391 |date=27 February 2020 |website=iefimerida.gr |language=el |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227113930/https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-deytero-thetiko-kroysma-stin-ellada-paidi-38hronis |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\":83\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-athina-trito-kroysma-stin-ellada-akyronontai-ola-ta-karnabalia |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0391\u03b8\u03ae\u03bd\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf \u03c4\u03c1\u03af\u03c4\u03bf \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 -\u0391\u03ba\u03c5\u03c1\u03ce\u03bd\u03bf\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03cc\u03bb\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b2\u03ac\u03bb\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 {{!}} \u0395\u039b\u039b\u0391\u0394\u0391 |date=27 February 2020 |website=iefimerida.gr |language=el |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227114026/https://www.iefimerida.gr/ellada/koronoios-athina-trito-kroysma-stin-ellada-akyronontai-ola-ta-karnabalia |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\":72\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ant1news.gr/ygeia-periballon/article/561073/koronoios-tria-kroysmata-stin-ellada-akyronontai-oi-ekdiloseis-gia-to-karnabali-se-oli-ti-xora |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03c4\u03c1\u03af\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 \u2013 \u0391\u03ba\u03c5\u03c1\u03ce\u03bd\u03bf\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03b5\u03ba\u03b4\u03b7\u03bb\u03ce\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf \u039a\u03b1\u03c1\u03bd\u03b1\u03b2\u03ac\u03bb\u03b9 \u03c3\u03b5 \u03cc\u03bb\u03b7 \u03c4\u03b7 \u03c7\u03ce\u03c1\u03b1 |website=antenna.gr |language=el |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227115401/https://www.ant1news.gr/ygeia-periballon/article/561073/koronoios-tria-kroysmata-stin-ellada-akyronontai-oi-ekdiloseis-gia-to-karnabali-se-oli-ti-xora |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Subsequent cases is Greece were mainly related to people who had travelled to Italy and a group of pilgrims who had travelled to Israel and Egypt, as well as their contacts.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/210074/koronoios-stin-ellada-sta-31-ta-kroysmata-toy-ioy-21-nea |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1: \u03a3\u03c4\u03b1 31 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u2013 21 \u03bd\u03ad\u03b1 |last=Newsroom |date=2020-03-05 |website=CNN.gr |language=el |access-date=2020-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323114331/https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/210074/koronoios-stin-ellada-sta-31-ta-kroysmata-toy-ioy-21-nea |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.newsit.gr/ellada/koronoios-14-akoma-krousmata-stin-ellad/2988717/ |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: 14 \u03b1\u03ba\u03cc\u03bc\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1! |website=www.newsit.gr |url-status=live |access-date=2020-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307063741/https://www.newsit.gr/ellada/koronoios-14-akoma-krousmata-stin-ellad/2988717/ |archive-date=7 March 2020 }}</ref> Health and state authorities issued precautionary guidelines and recommendations, while measures up to that point were taken locally and included the closure of schools and the suspension of cultural events in the affected areas (particularly [[Elis (regional unit)|Ilia]], [[Achaea]] and [[Zakynthos]]).<ref name=\":0\" /> The first confirmed death from COVID-19 in Greece was a 66-year-old man, who died on 12 March.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/greece-reports-first-coronavirus-death-66-year-old-man/ |title=Greece reports first coronavirus death, 66-year-old man |date=12 March 2020 |website=straitstimes.com |access-date=13 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314014704/https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/greece-reports-first-coronavirus-death-66-year-old-man |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nBy 15 April, there were 2192 confirmed cases in Greece, 102 deaths and 269 recoveries.<ref name=\"greececases\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.moh.gov.gr/articles/ministry/grafeio-typoy/press-releases/7083-enhmerwsh-diapisteymenwn-syntaktwn-ygeias-apo-ton-yfypoyrgo-politikhs-prostasias-kai-diaxeirishs-krisewn-niko-xardalia-kai-ton-ekproswpo-toy-ypoyrgeioy-ygeias-gia-to-neo-koronoio-kathhghth-swthrh-tsiodra-15-4-2020|title=\u0395\u03bd\u03b7\u03bc\u03ad\u03c1\u03c9\u03c3\u03b7 \u03b4\u03b9\u03b1\u03c0\u03b9\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c5\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03c9\u03bd \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03ba\u03c4\u03ce\u03bd \u03c5\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03a5\u03c6\u03c5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03cc \u03a0\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u0394\u03b9\u03b1\u03c7\u03b5\u03af\u03c1\u03b9\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 \u039a\u03c1\u03af\u03c3\u03b5\u03c9\u03bd \u039d\u03af\u03ba\u03bf \u03a7\u03b1\u03c1\u03b4\u03b1\u03bb\u03b9\u03ac \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u03b5\u03ba\u03c0\u03c1\u03cc\u03c3\u03c9\u03c0\u03bf \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03a5\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03bf\u03c5 \u03a5\u03b3\u03b5\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c4\u03bf \u03bd\u03ad\u03bf \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc, \u039a\u03b1\u03b8\u03b7\u03b3\u03b7\u03c4\u03ae \u03a3\u03c9\u03c4\u03ae\u03c1\u03b7 \u03a4\u03c3\u03b9\u03cc\u03b4\u03c1\u03b1 (15/4/2020)|last=|first=|date=2020-04-15|website=Ministry of Health|language=el|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref> The Greek [[National Public Health Organization (Greece)|National Public Health Organization]] (NPHO), in collaboration with local authorities and doctors, is tracking and testing everyone who came in close contact with the patients.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.onmed.gr/ygeia-eidhseis/story/382322/koronoios-stin-patra-to-enato-kroysma |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03b1\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u0388\u03bd\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03b2\u03b5\u03b2\u03b1\u03b9\u03c9\u03bc\u03ad\u03bd\u03bf \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03a0\u03ac\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1 |website=www.onmed.gr |language=el |access-date=23 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323114330/https://www.onmed.gr/ygeia-eidhseis/story/382322/koronoios-stin-patra-to-enato-kroysma |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ant1news.gr/ygeia-periballon/article/561722/koronoios-deka-ta-kroysmata-stin-ellada |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u0394\u03ad\u03ba\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 |website=antenna.gr |language=el |access-date=2020-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323114327/https://www.ant1news.gr/ygeia-periballon/article/561722/koronoios-deka-ta-kroysmata-stin-ellada |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> By March 10, with 89 confirmed cases and no deaths in the country, the government decided to suspend the operation of educational institutions of all levels nationwide and then, on 13 March, to close down all cafes, bars, museums, shopping centres, sports facilities and restaurants in the country.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.minedu.gov.gr/news/44308-10-03-20-prosorini-apagorefsi-tis-ekpaideftikis-leitourgias-olon-ton-ekpaideftikon-domon |title=\u03a5\u03a0\u039f\u03a5\u03a1\u0393\u0395\u0399\u039f \u03a0\u0391\u0399\u0394\u0395\u0399\u0391\u03a3 & \u0398\u03a1\u0397\u03a3\u039a\u0395\u03a5\u039c\u0391\u03a4\u03a9\u039d \u2013 10-03-20 \u03a0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c3\u03c9\u03c1\u03b9\u03bd\u03ae \u03b1\u03c0\u03b1\u03b3\u03cc\u03c1\u03b5\u03c5\u03c3\u03b7 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03b5\u03ba\u03c0\u03b1\u03b9\u03b4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ae\u03c2 \u03bb\u03b5\u03b9\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 \u03cc\u03bb\u03c9\u03bd \u03c4\u03c9\u03bd \u03b5\u03ba\u03c0\u03b1\u03b9\u03b4\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ce\u03bd \u03b4\u03bf\u03bc\u03ce\u03bd |website=www.minedu.gov.gr |access-date=2020-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323114328/https://www.minedu.gov.gr/news/44308-10-03-20-prosorini-apagorefsi-tis-ekpaideftikis-leitourgias-olon-ton-ekpaideftikon-domon |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.capital.gr/epikairotita/3437285/sta-190-sunolika-ta-krousmata-stin-ellada-kleinoun-emporika-kentra-kafe-mpar |title=\u03a3\u03c4\u03b1 190 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bd\u03bf\u03bb\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u03c4\u03b1 \u03ba\u03c1\u03bf\u03cd\u03c3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 \u2013 \u039a\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03b5\u03bc\u03c0\u03bf\u03c1\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u03ba\u03ad\u03bd\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1, \u03ba\u03b1\u03c6\u03ad, \u03bc\u03c0\u03b1\u03c1 |last=Capital.gr |website=Capital.gr |language=el |access-date=2020-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323114330/https://www.capital.gr/epikairotita/3437285/sta-190-sunolika-ta-krousmata-stin-ellada-kleinoun-emporika-kentra-kafe-mpar |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 16 March, all retail shops were also closed and all services in all areas of religious worship of any religion or dogma were suspended.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.news247.gr/koinonia/koronoios-kleinoyn-ta-emporika-katastimata-se-karantina-osoi-erchontai-apo-exoteriko.7603146.html |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u039a\u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03c4\u03b1 \u03b5\u03bc\u03c0\u03bf\u03c1\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac \u03ba\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03ae\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u2013 \u03a3\u03b5 \u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03af\u03bd\u03b1 \u03cc\u03c3\u03bf\u03b9 \u03ad\u03c1\u03c7\u03bf\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03b5\u03be\u03c9\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc |website=www.news247.gr |language=el |access-date=2020-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323114328/https://www.news247.gr/koinonia/koronoios-kleinoyn-ta-emporika-katastimata-se-karantina-osoi-erchontai-apo-exoteriko.7603146.html |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kathimerini.gr/1069449/article/epikairothta/politikh/anastellontai-oles-oi-8rhskeytikes-leitoyrgies-me-apofash-ths-kyvernhshs |title=\u0391\u03bd\u03b1\u03c3\u03c4\u03ad\u03bb\u03bb\u03bf\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03b9 \u03cc\u03bb\u03b5\u03c2 \u03bf\u03b9 \u03b8\u03c1\u03b7\u03c3\u03ba\u03b5\u03c5\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03ad\u03c2 \u03bb\u03b5\u03b9\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03af\u03b5\u03c2 \u03bc\u03b5 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc\u03c6\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7 \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03ba\u03c5\u03b2\u03ad\u03c1\u03bd\u03b7\u03c3\u03b7\u03c2 {{!}} Kathimerini |website=www.kathimerini.gr |access-date=2020-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317173105/https://www.kathimerini.gr/1069449/article/epikairothta/politikh/anastellontai-oles-oi-8rhskeytikes-leitoyrgies-me-apofash-ths-kyvernhshs |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 18 and 19 March, the government announced a series of measures of more than 10 billion euros to support the economy, businesses and employees.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ethnos.gr/oikonomia/94785_koronoios-ta-metra-gia-ergazomenoys-ki-epiheiriseis |title=\u039a\u03bf\u03c1\u03bf\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc\u03c2: \u03a4\u03b1 \u03bc\u03ad\u03c4\u03c1\u03b1 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03b5\u03c1\u03b3\u03b1\u03b6\u03cc\u03bc\u03b5\u03bd\u03bf\u03c5\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b9 \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03c7\u03b5\u03b9\u03c1\u03ae\u03c3\u03b5\u03b9\u03c2 |date=2020-03-18 |website=\u0388\u03b8\u03bd\u03bf\u03c2 |language=el |access-date=2020-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319180505/https://www.ethnos.gr/oikonomia/94785_koronoios-ta-metra-gia-ergazomenoys-ki-epiheiriseis |archive-date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 22 March the Greek authorities announced significant restrictions on all nonessential transport and movement across the country, starting from 6 a.m. on 23 March.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ekathimerini.com/250917/article/ekathimerini/news/full-lockdown-in-effect-from-monday-to-curb-coronavirus |title=Full lockdown in effect from Monday to curb coronavirus {{!}} Kathimerini |website=www.ekathimerini.com |language=English |access-date=2020-03-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323114329/http://www.ekathimerini.com/250917/article/ekathimerini/news/full-lockdown-in-effect-from-monday-to-curb-coronavirus |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Guernsey===\n{{Main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Guernsey}}\nOn 9 March, the first case in the crown dependency was confirmed.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.jerseyeveningpost.com/news/2020/03/09/first-case-of-coronavirus-confirmed-in-channel-islands/ |title=First case of coronavirus confirmed in Channel Islands |last=Maguire |first=Jack |website=www.jerseyeveningpost.com |language=en |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311111621/https://jerseyeveningpost.com/news/2020/03/09/first-case-of-coronavirus-confirmed-in-channel-islands/ |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== Hungary ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Hungary}}\nOn 4 March Prime Minister [[Viktor Orb\u00e1n]] announced that two Iranian students had been infected with the virus.<ref name=\"magyar.hirlap.1\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.magyarhirlap.hu/kronika/20200304-ket-koronavirusos-beteg-van-magyarorszagon |title=K\u00e9t koronav\u00edrusos beteg van Magyarorsz\u00e1gon |access-date=4 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321011517/https://www.magyarhirlap.hu/kronika/20200304-ket-koronavirusos-beteg-van-magyarorszagon |archive-date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The students are asymptomatic and have been transported to Saint Ladislaus Hospital in [[Budapest]].<ref name=\"magyar.hirlap.1\" />\n\n=== Iceland ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iceland}}\nThe first case was confirmed in Iceland on 28 February, an Icelandic male in his forties who had been on a ski trip to Andalo in Northern Italy and returned home on 22 February.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ruv.is/frett/fyrsta-tilfelli-covid-19-greint-a-islandi |title=Fyrsta tilfelli COVID-19 greint \u00e1 \u00cdslandi |date=28 February 2020 |language=is |trans-title=First COVID-19 case diagnosed in Iceland |access-date=28 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228154743/https://www.ruv.is/frett/fyrsta-tilfelli-covid-19-greint-a-islandi |archive-date=28 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIceland's Department of Civil Protection and Emergency Management declared a state of emergency on 6 March after two cases of community transmission in Iceland were confirmed, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 43.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.almannavarnir.is/frettir/neydarstig-almannavarna-vegna-covid-19/ |title=Ney\u00f0arstig almannavarna vegna COVID-19 |date=6 March 2020 |website=Almannavarnir (Department of Civil Protection and Emergency Management) |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323170955/https://www.almannavarnir.is/frettir/neydarstig-almannavarna-vegna-covid-19/ |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 13 March, it was announced at an official press conference that a four-week ban on public gatherings of more than 100 persons would be put into effect as of Monday 16 March. Universities and secondary schools will be closed for four weeks. International airports and harbours will remain exempt from these measures.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ruv.is/frett/bladamannafundur-heilbrigdisradherra |title=Bla\u00f0amannafundur heilbrig\u00f0isr\u00e1\u00f0herra |date=13 March 2020 |language=is |access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Ireland ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Republic of Ireland}}\nThe National Public Health Emergency Team of Ireland announced that a case in Ireland has been confirmed on 29 February.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.rte.ie/news/coronavirus/2020/0229/1119357-coronavirus-ireland/ |title=First case of Covid-19 diagnosed in east of Ireland |date=1 March 2020 |work=[[RT\u00c9 News and Current Affairs]] |access-date=2 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301185230/https://www.rte.ie/news/coronavirus/2020/0229/1119357-coronavirus-ireland/ |archive-date=1 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"ireland.1\">[https://bnonews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/ireland.png Statement from...] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229210449/https://bnonews.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/ireland.png |date=29 February 2020 }} ''bnonews.com'', accessed 12 March 2020</ref> Response to the outbreak has included cancellation of [[Saint Patrick's Day|St Patrick's Day]] parades and all festivals.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51806551 |title=Irish St Patrick's Day parades off over coronavirus |date=9 March 2020 |work=BBC News |access-date=9 March 2020 |language=en-GB |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309230026/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-51806551 |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 12 March, all schools, universities and childcare institutes were closed until 29 March. On 20 March emergency legislation was signed into law by [[Michael D. Higgins]] giving the state permission to [[Detention (imprisonment)|detain]] people, restrict travel and keep people in their homes to help combat the spread of the pandemic.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Kenny |first=Aisling |url=https://www.rte.ie/news/coronavirus/2020/0320/1124275-covid19-coronavirus-politics/ |title=President Higgins signs emergency measures into law |date=20 March 2020 |work=RTE |url-status=live |access-date=20 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321010748/https://www.rte.ie/news/coronavirus/2020/0320/1124275-covid19-coronavirus-politics/ |archive-date=21 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\nAs of 28 March, there have been 2,415 confirmed cases and 36 deaths.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Dwyer |first=Orla |url=https://www.thejournal.ie/new-confirmed-coronavirus-cases-5060907-Mar2020/ |title=Coronavirus: 14 more deaths and 294 new cases in Ireland confirmed |date=28 March 2020 |work=[[TheJournal.ie]] |access-date=28 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328184437/https://www.thejournal.ie/new-confirmed-coronavirus-cases-5060907-Mar2020/ |archive-date=28 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== Italy ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy}}\nOn 31 January, the first two cases were confirmed in [[Rome]]. Two Chinese tourists, who arrived in [[Milan]] on 23 January via [[Milan Malpensa Airport]] and travelled to [[Rome]] on a tourist bus, tested positive for and were hospitalised in [[Lazzaro Spallanzani National Institute for Infectious Diseases]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_gennaio_30/coronavirus-italia-corona-9d6dc436-4343-11ea-bdc8-faf1f56f19b7.shtml |title=Coronavirus, primi due casi in Italia: sono due turisti cinesi |date=30 January 2020 |website=Corriere della Sera |language=it |access-date=28 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200217050130/https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_gennaio_30/coronavirus-italia-corona-9d6dc436-4343-11ea-bdc8-faf1f56f19b7.shtml |archive-date=17 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 6 February, one of the Italians repatriated from [[Wuhan]], China tested positive, bringing the total number of cases in Italy to three.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Jessie Yeung |url=https://www.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-02-06-20-intl-hnk/index.html |title=February 6 coronavirus news |date=6 February 2020 |publisher=CNN |last2=Adam Renton |last3=Steve George |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206161214/https://www.cnn.com/asia/live-news/coronavirus-outbreak-02-06-20-intl-hnk/index.html |archive-date=6 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 22 February, the repatriated Italian recovered and was discharged from the hospital.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.open.online/2020/02/22/coronavirus-bollettino-dello-spallanzani-guarito-il-ricercatore-italiano-verra-dimesso-oggi/ |title=Coronavirus, bollettino dello Spallanzani: guarito il ricercatore italiano, verr\u00e0 dimesso oggi. Niccol\u00f2 \"sta benissimo\" \u2013 Il video |date=22 February 2020 |website=Open |language=it-IT |access-date=23 February 2020 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200224202651/https://www.open.online/2020/02/22/coronavirus-bollettino-dello-spallanzani-guarito-il-ricercatore-italiano-verra-dimesso-oggi/ |archive-date=24 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 22 and 26 February, the two Chinese tourists hospitalized in Rome tested negative.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/mondo/coronavirus_diretta_morti_contagi_oggi_ultime_notizie_26_febbraio_2020-5075865.html |title=Coronavirus, diretta. Contagi a quota 424, primo caso in Puglia, 12 morti. Lombardia, Fontana \u00e8 negativo, ma resta in isolamento per 14 giorni |website=www.ilmessaggero.it |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228064053/https://www.ilmessaggero.it/mondo/coronavirus_diretta_morti_contagi_oggi_ultime_notizie_26_febbraio_2020-5075865.html |archive-date=28 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 21 February, a cluster of cases was detected starting with 16 confirmed cases in [[Lombardy]],<ref name=\"ThomReut_IT_16cluster_21Feb\">{{Cite news |last=Anzolin |first=Elisa |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-italy/coronavirus-outbreak-grows-in-northern-italy-16-cases-reported-in-one-day-idUSKBN20F0UI |title=Coronavirus outbreak grows in northern Italy, 16 cases reported in one day |date=21 February 2020 |access-date=21 February 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221225322/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-italy/coronavirus-outbreak-grows-in-northern-italy-16-cases-reported-in-one-day-idUSKBN20F0UI |archive-date=21 February 2020 |agency=[[Thomson Reuters]] |last2=Amante |first2=Angelo}}</ref> with additional 60 cases on 22 February,<ref name=\"CorrieredSera_76_recent_cases\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-italia-nuovi-contagi-lombardia-veneto-245e72d4-5540-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml |title=Coronavirus: primi casi a Milano. Cosa sappiamo dei nuovi contagi in Lombardia, Veneto e Piemonte |date=2020-02-22 |work=[[Corriere della Sera]] |access-date=2020-02-22 |url-status=live |url-access=<!-- (subscription/registration/limited) default=free  |dead |unfit |usurped --> |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222225105/https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-italia-nuovi-contagi-lombardia-veneto-245e72d4-5540-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml |archive-date=22 February 2020 }}</ref> and Italy's first deaths reported on the same day.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/adriano_trevisan_la_prima_vittima_di_coronavirus_in_italia-249260446/ |title=Adriano Trevisan, la prima vittima di coronavirus in Italia |date=22 February 2020 |website=la Repubblica |language=it |access-date=28 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226235609/https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/adriano_trevisan_la_prima_vittima_di_coronavirus_in_italia-249260446/ |archive-date=26 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> As of late February, Italy was hit harder than anywhere else in the EU by the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] outbreak.<ref name=\"politico-italy\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/politics-goes-viral-as-italy-struggles-with-outbreak/ |title=Politics goes viral as Italy struggles with outbreak |last=Borrelli |first=Silvia Sciorilli |date=25 February 2020 |website=POLITICO |access-date=26 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nAs of 17 March 2020, there have been 2,503 deaths and 31,506 confirmed cases.<ref name=\"Min_Salute_Situazione\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.salute.gov.it/portale/nuovocoronavirus/dettaglioContenutiNuovoCoronavirus.jsp?lingua=italiano&id=5351&area=nuovoCoronavirus&menu=vuoto |title=Covid-19 \u2013 Situazione in Italia |website=www.salute.gov.it |publisher=Ministero della Salute |language=it |access-date=13 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321172727/http://www.salute.gov.it/portale/nuovocoronavirus/dettaglioContenutiNuovoCoronavirus.jsp?lingua=italiano&id=5351&area=nuovoCoronavirus&menu=vuoto |archive-date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==== Lockdown ====\n{{main|2020 Italy coronavirus lockdown}}\n8 March: In the early hours of Sunday, Italian prime minister Giuseppe Conte signed a decree enacting forced quarantine for the region of Lombardy \u2013 home to more than 10 million people and the financial capital, Milan \u2013 and multiple other provinces, totalling around 16 million residents. The lockdown decree included the power to impose fines on anyone caught entering or leaving Lombardy, the worst-affected region, until 3 April.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/08/coronavirus-italy-quarantine-virus-reaches-washington-dc |title=Coronavirus: quarter of Italy's population put in quarantine as virus reaches Washington DC |date=8 March 2020 |via=www.theguardian.com |access-date=8 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308060523/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/08/coronavirus-italy-quarantine-virus-reaches-washington-dc |archive-date=8 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 9 March in the evening, the lockdown orders were extended to the whole of Italy, effectively quarantining more than 60 million people.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51810673 Coronavirus: Italy extends emergency measures nationwide] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309223037/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-51810673 |date=9 March 2020 }} 10 March 2020 ''www.bbc.co.uk'', accessed 12 March 2020</ref>\n\n=== Kosovo ===\n{{Main| 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Kosovo}}\nThe first two cases were reported in the country on 13 March. In the ten-day period March 13\u201323, the number of positive cases with coronavirus rose to 35. In midnight of 23 March, 26 new cases were confirmed, bringing the total number of cases to 61.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://telegrafi.com/26-raste-te-reja-covid-19-shkon-ne-59-numri-te-infektuarve-ne-kosove/ |title=From 35 to 61 cases in Kosovo with COVID-19, 26 more unexpected cases |date=23 March 2020 |language=sq |access-date=23 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323235503/https://telegrafi.com/26-raste-te-reja-covid-19-shkon-ne-59-numri-te-infektuarve-ne-kosove/ |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On March 25, the government collapsed with a vote of no confidence in Prime Minister Albin Kurti after the Prime Minister refused to call a state of emergency to deal with the COVID-19 crisis.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-52044136 |title=Coronavirus row helps topple Kosovo government |date=26 March 2020 |language=en |access-date=26 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326062956/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-52044136 |archive-date=26 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== Latvia ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Latvia}}\n\n=== Liechtenstein ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Liechtenstein}}\nThe first case was reported in the country on 3 March.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n=== Lithuania ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Lithuania}}\nThe first case was reported in the country on 28 February. By March 17 there were 21 cases, mostly in Vilnius, Kaunas and Klaip\u0117da. The first infected Lithuanian recovered on 14 March.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.lrt.lt/naujienos/lietuvoje/2/1151427/skvernelis-pranese-kad-sestadieni-bus-priimtas-sprendimas-del-karantino-salies-mastu|title=Skvernelis prane\u0161\u0117, kad \u0161e\u0161tadien\u012f bus priimtas sprendimas d\u0117l karantino \u0161alies mastu|date=14 March 2020|website=lrt.lt|language=lt-LT|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Luxembourg ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Luxembourg}}\nThe first case was reported in the country on 29 February.\n\n=== Malta ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Malta}}\nOn 7 March, Malta reported its first 3 cases of coronavirus: an Italian family consisting of a 12-year-old girl and her parents, who arrived in Malta on 3 March from Rome after a holiday in Trentino.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofmalta.com/articles/view/first-coronavirus-case-reported-in-malta.776288 |title=First coronavirus case reported in Malta |date=7 March 2020 |work=[[Times of Malta]] |access-date=7 March 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307233527/https://timesofmalta.com/articles/view/first-coronavirus-case-reported-in-malta.776288 |archive-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Moldova ===\n<!-- \nPlease, do not remove the link to Transnistria, Transnistrian cases are treated in its own article\n -->\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Moldova|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Transnistria|l2=Transnistria}}\nOn 7 March, the first case was confirmed in the [[Moldova|Republic of Moldova]]: a 48-year-old woman who had recently returned from [[Italy]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://deschide.md/ro/stiri/social/62248/BREAKING-NEWS-Primul-caz-de-coronavirus-depistat-%C3%AEn-Republica-Moldova-O-femeie-de-48-de-ani-infectat%C4%83.htm |title=BREAKING NEWS// Primul caz de coronavirus depistat \u00een Republica Moldova. O femeie de 48 de ani, infectat\u0103 |date=7 March 2020 |website=Deschide.md |language=ro |trans-title=BREAKING NEWS// First coronavirus case detected in Republic of Moldova. A 48-year-old woman, infected |access-date=7 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327121917/https://deschide.md/ro/stiri/social/62248/BREAKING-NEWS-Primul-caz-de-coronavirus-depistat-%25C3%25AEn-Republica-Moldova-O-femeie-de-48-de-ani-infectat%25C4%2583.htm |archive-date=27 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Three days later, another two cases were confirmed.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/alte-doua-cazuri-de-imbolnaviri-cu-infectia-coronovirus-de-tip-nou-pe-teritoriul-tarii |title=Alte dou\u0103 cazuri de \u00eemboln\u0103viri cu infec\u021bia Coronovirus de tip nou, pe teritoriul \u021b\u0103rii. Viorica Dumbr\u0103veanu \u00eendeamn\u0103 cet\u0103\u021benii s\u0103 respecte recomand\u0103rile autorit\u0103\u021bilor |date=10 March 2020 |website=msmps.gov.md |publisher=[[Ministry of Health, Labour and Social Protection (Moldova)]] |language=ro |trans-title=Another two cases of a new-type coronavirus in a country. Viorica Dumbr\u0103veanu urges citizens to respect the guidelines of authorities |access-date=10 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323135845/https://msmps.gov.md/ro/content/alte-doua-cazuri-de-imbolnaviri-cu-infectia-coronovirus-de-tip-nou-pe-teritoriul-tarii |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn the other hand, on 21 March, the first two cases in the unrecognized republic of [[Transnistria]] (officially part of Moldova) were confirmed.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Soltan |first=Irina |url=https://agora.md/stiri/68629/au-fost-confirmate-14-cazuri-noi-de-infectie-cu-covid19-bilantul-imbolnavirilor-se-ridica-la-80-de-persoane |title=Au fost confirmate 14 cazuri noi de infec\u021bie cu COVID-19. Bilan\u021bul \u00eemboln\u0103virilor se ridic\u0103 la 80 de persoane |date=21 March 2020 |work=Agora |language=Romanian |access-date=30 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330023653/https://agora.md/stiri/68629/au-fost-confirmate-14-cazuri-noi-de-infectie-cu-covid19-bilantul-imbolnavirilor-se-ridica-la-80-de-persoane |archive-date=30 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== Monaco ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Monaco}}\nThe first case was reported in the country on 29 February.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n=== Montenegro ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Montenegro}}\n\n=== Netherlands ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Netherlands}}\n\nOn 27 February, the [[Netherlands]] confirmed its first case, a man who had been in the Lombardy region of Italy.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rivm.nl/nieuws/patient-met-nieuw-coronavirus-in-nederland |title=Pati\u00ebnt met nieuw coronavirus in Nederland &#124; RIVM |date=27 February 2020 |website=www.rivm.nl |access-date=3 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227205021/https://www.rivm.nl/nieuws/patient-met-nieuw-coronavirus-in-nederland |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 6 March, [[Netherlands National Institute for Public Health and the Environment|RIVM]] announced the first death.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://nltimes.nl/2020/03/06/first-coronavirus-fatality-netherlands-rotterdam-patient-dead-86 |title=First coronavirus fatality in Netherlands: Rotterdam patient dead at 86 |date=6 March 2020 |website=nltimes.nl |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200408115958/https://nltimes.nl/2020/03/06/first-coronavirus-fatality-netherlands-rotterdam-patient-dead-86 |archive-date=8 April 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 9 March, RIVM announced 56 more confirmed cases in addition to the total of the 77 infected patients declared in the previous day, bringing the total to 321 infected and 3 dead.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nu.nl/coronavirus/6035907/nog-twee-coronaviruspatienten-in-nederland-overleden-in-totaal-265-besmettingen.html |title=Nog twee pati\u00ebnten overleden door coronavirus, in totaal 264 infecties |date=8 March 2020 |website=www.nu.nl}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, the Dutch government announced in a press conference that all schools, day care facilities, colleges, universities, and universities of applied sciences would close until 6 April. Though children of parents in vital industries could still go to school or the day care if they could not be taken care of otherwise.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nu.nl/coronavirus/6037745/scholen-dicht-veel-leraren-staan-klaar-om-er-het-beste-van-te-maken |title=Scholen dicht: 'Veel leraren staan klaar om er het beste van te maken' |date=16 March 2020 |website=www.nu.nl}}</ref>\n\nAs of 16 March, the total number of confirmed cases of COVID-19 had risen to 1,413. The total number of confirmed deaths had risen to 24. This was an increase of 278 infections and 4 deaths in comparison to 15 March.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nu.nl/coronavirus/6037865/278-nieuwe-bevestigde-besmettingen-in-nederland-dodental-naar-24.html |title=278 nieuwe bevestigde besmettingen in Nederland, dodental naar 24 |date=16 March 2020 |website=www.nu.nl |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317060610/https://www.nu.nl/coronavirus/6037865/278-nieuwe-bevestigde-besmettingen-in-nederland-dodental-naar-24.html |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn the same date, the Minister President, [[Mark Rutte]], of the Netherlands had announced that the country would not go into complete lockdown. Instead the situation would be controlled as much as possible by delaying the spread of the virus, relying on measures taken earlier by the government, such as social distancing and prohibiting gatherings of 100 people and over.<ref name=\"approach-NL\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.government.nl/topics/coronavirus-covid-19/tackling-new-coronavirus-in-the-netherlands |title=The approach to tackling coronavirus in the Netherlands \u2013 Coronavirus COVID-19 |date=2020-03-19 |website=www.government.nl |publisher=Government of the Netherlands |language=en-GB |access-date=2020-03-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325205834/https://www.government.nl/topics/coronavirus-covid-19/tackling-new-coronavirus-in-the-netherlands |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> It is expected the coronavirus will keep spreading and a large part of the population will become infected. Instead of opting to lockdown the Netherlands for the time required, which would have a lot of (negative) consequences while the benefits remain uncertain and would have to stay in place, it will be attempted to build herd immunity in a controlled manner. Depending on how the virus behaves, the government will decide if additional measures are required.<ref name=\"approach-NL\" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nu.nl/coronavirus/6037995/rutte-groot-deel-van-nederlanders-zal-besmet-raken-met-coronavirus.html |title=Rutte: Groot deel van Nederlanders zal besmet raken met coronavirus |date=16 March 2020 |access-date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317060633/https://www.nu.nl/coronavirus/6037995/rutte-groot-deel-van-nederlanders-zal-besmet-raken-met-coronavirus.html |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nFurther measures were introduced on 23 March. All events will be banned until 1 June. Gatherings of more than three people, except for families, are prohibited. City mayors received greater authorisation to enforce the rules. Fines will be issued to those not complying with the new rules.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.volkskrant.nl/gs-b2ea8620 |title=Geen Koningsdag en eredivisie, forse boetes en strenge handhaving |last=Mis\u00e9rus |first=Mark |last2=Dirks |first2=Bart |date=2020-03-23 |website=de Volkskrant |language=nl-NL |access-date=2020-03-24 |last3=Kreling |first3=Tom}}</ref>\n\n=== North Macedonia ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in North Macedonia}}\nOn 26 February, [[North Macedonia]] confirmed its first case, a woman that had returned from Italy.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n=== Norway ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Norway}}\n[[File:Coronavirus-separation-on-bus-Trondheim 01.jpg|thumb|Separation of an area near the driver, bus in [[Trondheim]], 15 March]]\nOn 26 February, [[Norway]] confirmed its first case, in a person who had returned from [[China]] the previous week.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fhi.no/en/news/2020/one-person-has-tested-positive-for-coronavirus/ |title=One person has tested positive for coronavirus |website=Norwegian Institute of Public Health |access-date=26 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226221626/https://www.fhi.no/en/news/2020/one-person-has-tested-positive-for-coronavirus/ |archive-date=26 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.thelocal.no/20200226/breaking-norway-announces-first-case-of-coronavirus |title=Norway announces first case of coronavirus |website=thelocal.no |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227015517/https://www.thelocal.no/20200226/breaking-norway-announces-first-case-of-coronavirus |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 7 March, there were 147 confirmed cases in [[Norway]]. Most of the cases could either be linked to outbreaks abroad or close encounters with these. Altogether 89 have been infected on travel in [[Italy]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fhi.no/nyheter/2020/status-koronavirus-lordag-72.-mars-2020/ |title=Status koronavirus l\u00f8rdag 7. mars 2020 |website=Norwegian Institute of Public Health |language=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308191051/https://www.fhi.no/nyheter/2020/status-koronavirus-lordag-72.-mars-2020/ |archive-date=8 March 2020 |access-date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 March 2020, all kindergartens, schools, colleges and universities were closed until at least 26 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.helsedirektoratet.no/nyheter/the-norwegian-directorate-of-health-has-issued-a-decision-to-close-schools-and-other-educational-institutions |title=The Norwegian Directorate of Health has issued a decision to close schools and other educational institutions |website=helsedirektoratet.no |publisher=The Norwegian Directorate of Health |access-date=13 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327072503/https://www.helsedirektoratet.no/nyheter/the-norwegian-directorate-of-health-has-issued-a-decision-to-close-schools-and-other-educational-institutions |archive-date=27 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== Poland ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Poland}}\n\n=== Portugal ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Portugal}}\nOn 2 March, the first two cases were confirmed in [[Portugal]], both in the city of [[Porto]]. One was a doctor that had returned from holiday in northern Italy and the other a worker from Spain.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-portugal/portugal-registers-first-two-cases-of-coronavirus-health-minister-idUSKBN20P1BB |title=Portugal registers first two cases of coronavirus: Health minister |date=2 March 2020 |work=Reuters |access-date=2 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302115848/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-portugal/portugal-registers-first-two-cases-of-coronavirus-health-minister-idUSKBN20P1BB |archive-date=2 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/03/02/world/europe/02reuters-health-coronavirus-portugal.html |title=Portugal Registers First Two Cases of Coronavirus: Health Minister |date=2 March 2020 |work=The New York Times |access-date=2 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302115833/https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/03/02/world/europe/02reuters-health-coronavirus-portugal.html |archive-date=2 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, the [[President of Portugal|President of the Republic]], [[Marcelo Rebelo de Sousa]], declared the entirety of the Portuguese territory in a [[State of emergency#Portugal|state of emergency]] for the following fifteen days, with the possibility of renewal, the first since the [[Carnation Revolution]] in 1974.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.presidencia.pt/?idc=22&idi=176060 |title=Mensagem do Presidente da Rep\u00fablica ao Pa\u00eds sobre a declara\u00e7\u00e3o do estado de emerg\u00eancia (Pal\u00e1cio de Bel\u00e9m, 18 de mar\u00e7o de 2020) |date=18 March 2020 |website=Presidency of the Portuguese Republic |language=pt |trans-title=Message of the President of the Republic to the Country on the declaration of a state of emergency |access-date=18 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318212455/http://www.presidencia.pt/?idc=22&idi=176060 |archive-date=18 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March the Portuguese Government admitted that the country could not contain anymore the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] as it is wide spreading and will enter the 'Mitigation Phase' on 26 March.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://expresso.pt/coronavirus/2020-03-24-Portugal-em-fase-de-mitigacao-a-partir-de-quinta-feira |title=Portugal em fase de mitiga\u00e7\u00e3o a partir de quinta-feira |date=24 March 2020 |work=Expresso |url-status=live |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324153727/https://expresso.pt/coronavirus/2020-03-24-Portugal-em-fase-de-mitigacao-a-partir-de-quinta-feira |archive-date=24 March 2020 }}</ref>\n\n=== Romania ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Romania}}\n\n=== Russia ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Russia}}\n[[File:Vladimir Putin in Kommunarka hospital1.jpg|thumb|Russian President [[Vladimir Putin]] visits coronavirus patients at Moscow hospital on 24 March]]\nRussia implemented preventive measures to curb the spread of COVID-19 in the country by imposing quarantines, carrying raids on potential virus carriers and using facial recognition to impose quarantine measures.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-moscow-deportation-idUSKCN20M252 |title=Russia to deport 88 foreigners for violating coronavirus quarantine |date=28 February 2020 |work=Reuters |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229030207/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-moscow-deportation-idUSKCN20M252 |archive-date=29 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 31 January, two cases were confirmed, one in [[Tyumen Oblast]], another in [[Zabaykalsky Krai]]. Both were Chinese nationals, who have since recovered.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/7656549 |title=\u0412 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u0432\u044b\u044f\u0432\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044b\u0435 \u0434\u0432\u0430 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u044f \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |date=31 January 2020 |access-date=31 January 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131125707/https://tass.ru/obschestvo/7656549 |archive-date=31 January 2020 |agency=TASS}}</ref><ref name=\":4\" />\n\nOn 2 March, the first case in the Moscow region was confirmed.<ref name=\"moscow.1\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.interfax.ru/russia/697390 |title=\u0423 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0435\u0445\u0430\u0432\u0448\u0435\u0433\u043e \u0438\u0437 \u0418\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0438 \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043e\u0431\u043d\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0436\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 |website=Interfax.ru |access-date=2 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319195614/https://www.interfax.ru/russia/697390 |archive-date=19 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ria.ru/20200302/1566843474.html |title=\u0423 \u0432\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0443\u0432\u0448\u0435\u0433\u043e\u0441\u044f \u0438\u0437 \u0418\u0442\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0438 \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u044b\u044f\u0432\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u2013 \u0420\u0418\u0410 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438, 02.03.2020<!-- Bot generated title --> |access-date=2 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304103919/https://ria.ru/20200302/1566843474.html |archive-date=4 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 7 March, four new cases were confirmed, three was in [[Lipetsk]] and one in [[Saint Petersburg]]. All people visited Italy in the previous two weeks.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://tass.ru/obschestvo/7923533 |title=\u0427\u0435\u0442\u044b\u0440\u0435 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0445 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u044f \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u044b \u0432 \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0441\u0443\u0442\u043a\u0438 |last=<!--Not stated--> |date=7 March 2020 |language=Russian |trans-title=Four new cases of coronavirus infection registered in Russia in the last day |access-date=7 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307120559/https://tass.ru/obschestvo/7923533 |archive-date=7 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 8 March, three news cases were confirmed, in [[Moscow Oblast|Moscow]], [[Belgorod Oblast|Belgorod]] and [[Kaliningrad Oblast|Kaliningrad]] Oblasts. All people returned from Italy.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ren.tv/news/v-rossii/670570-plius-tri-v-rf-zafiksirovany-novye-sluchai-zabolevaniia-koronavirusom |title=\u041f\u043b\u044e\u0441 \u0442\u0440\u0438: \u0432 \u0420\u0424 \u0437\u0430\u0444\u0438\u043a\u0441\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043d\u044b \u043d\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0435 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043e\u043c |last=<!--Not stated--> |date=9 March 2020 |language=Russian |trans-title=Plus three: new cases of coronavirus disease were recorded in Russian Federation |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309070110/https://ren.tv/news/v-rossii/670570-plius-tri-v-rf-zafiksirovany-novye-sluchai-zabolevaniia-koronavirusom |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 10 March, Moscow Mayor [[Sergey Sobyanin]] signed a decree for banning mass events in [[Moscow]] with more than 5000 participants from 10 March to 10 April.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.mos.ru/news/item/70786073/ |title=\u0412 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0430\u0442 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u0441\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0435 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0440\u0438\u044f\u0442\u0438\u044f \u0441 \u0447\u0438\u0441\u043b\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c\u044e \u0431\u043e\u043b\u0435\u0435 \u043f\u044f\u0442\u0438 \u0442\u044b\u0441\u044f\u0447 \u0447\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043a |date=5 February 2020 |work=mos.ru |access-date=12 March 2020 |language=ru |trans-title=Mass events in Moscow with more than 5000 participants will be limited. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317021018/https://www.mos.ru/news/item/70786073/ |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== San Marino ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in San Marino}}\nOn 27 February, [[San Marino]] confirmed its first case, an 88-year-old man with pre-existing medical conditions, who came from Italy. He was hospitalised at a hospital in [[Rimini]], Italy.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.altarimini.it/News132152-coronavirus-primo-caso-nella-repubblica-di-san-marino.php |title=Coronavirus: primo caso nella Repubblica di San Marino |date=2020-02-27 |website=Altarimini.it |language=it |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228000831/https://www.altarimini.it/News132152-coronavirus-primo-caso-nella-repubblica-di-san-marino.php |archive-date=28 February 2020 |access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> As of 25 March 2020: With 208 confirmed cases out of a population of 33,344 (as of 2018), it is the country with the highest percentage of confirmed cases per capita at {{formatnum:{{#expr: 208 / 33344 * 100 round 2}}%}} \u2013 1 confirmed case per {{formatnum:{{#expr: ceil(33344 / 208)}}}} inhabitants.<ref name=\"sm\">[[Template:2019-20 coronavirus pandemic data/San Marino medical cases chart]]</ref> Also, with 21 confirmed deaths, the country has the highest rate of confirmed deaths per capita at {{formatnum:{{#expr: 21 * 100 / 33344 round 3}}%}} of the total population \u2013 1 death per {{formatnum:{{#expr: ceil(33344 / 21)}}}} inhabitants.<ref name=\"sm\" /><!-- Copied content from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in San Marino]]; see that page's history for attribution. Someone please make a dynamic link to the text on that page, I've forgotten how to. -->\n\n===Serbia===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Serbia}}\n[[File:Disinfection during the Corona Pandemic in Serbia 2020.ogg|thumb|Disinfection of housing in [[Serbia]] during the 2020 coronavirus pandemic]]\nOn 29 February, a massive infection occurred in the town of [[Valjevo]] after a private party involving a guest from [[Austria]] who had previously stayed in [[Italy]].<ref>[https://rs-lat.sputniknews.com/zivot/202003261122175600-nemir-kruze-crne-vesti-preti-blokada-kako-je-bas-valjevo-postalo-veliko-zariste-korone-u-srbiji-virus-krusik/ Nemir, kru\u017ee crne vesti, preti blokada: Kako je ba\u0161 Valjevo postalo veliko \u017eari\u0161te korone u Srbiji] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327061438/https://rs-lat.sputniknews.com/zivot/202003261122175600-nemir-kruze-crne-vesti-preti-blokada-kako-je-bas-valjevo-postalo-veliko-zariste-korone-u-srbiji-virus-krusik/ |date=27 March 2020 }} ''rs-lat.sputniknews.com'', accessed 27 March 2020</ref><ref>[https://www.danas.rs/drustvo/nestorovic-zbog-neodgovornih-pojedinaca-moguca-izolacija-valjeva/ Nestorovi\u0107: Zbog neodgovornih pojedinaca mogu\u0107a izolacija Valjeva] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327071044/https://www.danas.rs/drustvo/nestorovic-zbog-neodgovornih-pojedinaca-moguca-izolacija-valjeva/ |date=27 March 2020 }} ''www.danas.rs'', accessed 27 March 2020</ref> On 6 March, the first case was confirmed in [[Serbia]] by Minister of Health [[Zlatibor Lon\u010dar]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-healthcare-coronavirus-serbia-idUSKBN20T152 |title=Serbia reports first case of coronavirus \u2013 health minister |date=6 March 2020 |work=Reuters |access-date=6 March 2020 |via=www.reuters.com |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308011518/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-healthcare-coronavirus-serbia-idUSKBN20T152 |archive-date=8 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> of a man who had traveled to [[Budapest]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/health-pmn/serbia-reports-first-case-of-coronavirus-health-minister |title=Serbia reports first case of coronavirus \u2013 health minister |last=Health |first=P. M. N. |date=6 March 2020 |access-date=6 March 2020}}</ref> President Aleksandar Vucic and the Government of the Republic of Serbia introduced a state of emergency on March 15. Two days later, curfew and quarantine were introduced as safeguards against massive infection.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n=== Slovakia ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Slovakia}}\n[[File:Berg a DNV - 49655368166.jpg|thumb|A queue of cars and trucks waiting to cross the Slovak border on 13 March]]\n[[File:Koronav\u00edrus - Bratislavsk\u00fd samospr\u00e1vny kraj (49669583963).jpg|thumb|People in [[Bratislava]] wearing masks on 16 March]]\nOn 6 March Slovakia confirmed its first case, a 52-year-old man coming from a small town nearby [[Bratislava]]. He had not travelled anywhere in recent weeks but his son had visited [[Venice]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-slovakia/slovakia-reports-first-case-of-coronavirus-prime-minister-idUSKBN20T1D8 |title=Slovakia reports first case of coronavirus |date=6 March 2020 |work=Reuters |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306151935/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-slovakia/slovakia-reports-first-case-of-coronavirus-prime-minister-idUSKBN20T1D8 |archive-date=6 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> His son didn't show any symptoms. On 7 March, the virus was also confirmed in his wife and son.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://domov.sme.sk/c/22352395/koronovirus-na-slovensku-pribudli-dva-pripady.html |title=Slovensko m\u00e1 tri pr\u00edpady koronav\u00edrusu, identifikovali aj pacienta 0 |last=a.s |first=Petit Press |website=domov.sme.sk |language=sk |access-date=7 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308195618/https://domov.sme.sk/c/22352395/koronovirus-na-slovensku-pribudli-dva-pripady.html |archive-date=8 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n=== Slovenia ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Slovenia}}\nOn 4 March Slovenia confirmed its first case. A patient of about 60 years of age had returned from Morocco few days earlier (via Italy) and was admitted to a hospital in [[Ljubljana]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://english.sta.si/2735036/first-case-of-coronavirus-infection-confirmed-in-slovenia |title=First case of coronavirus infection confirmed in Slovenia |date=4 March 2020 |work=[[Slovenian Press Agency]] |access-date=4 March 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200304221417/https://english.sta.si/2735036/first-case-of-coronavirus-infection-confirmed-in-slovenia |archive-date=4 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/health-pmn/slovenia-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus-health-minister |title=Slovenia confirms first case of coronavirus -health minister |date=4 March 2020 |access-date=4 March 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200304221712/https://nationalpost.com/pmn/health-pmn/slovenia-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus-health-minister |archive-date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 March, a total of eight cases were reported, three of them medical professionals, who contracted the virus on holiday in Italy. By 9 March, 16 people were confirmed to be infected.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\n=== Spain ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Spain}}\n[[File:Televisions Coronavirus Hospital.jpg|thumb|Television cameras covering the first coronavirus cases in a hospital in [[Valencia]]]]\nOn 31 January, Spain confirmed its first case, in the [[Canary Islands|Canary Island]] of [[La Gomera]]. A tourist from Germany tested positive and was admitted to [[Hospital Universitario Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de Candelaria|University Hospital of the Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de Candelaria]].<ref name=\":32\">{{cite web |url=https://elpais.com/sociedad/2020/01/31/actualidad/1580509404_469734.html |title=Sanidad confirma en La Gomera el primer caso de coronavirus en Espa\u00f1a |date=31 January 2020 |website=El Pais |language=es |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131225909/https://elpais.com/sociedad/2020/01/31/actualidad/1580509404_469734.html |archive-date=31 January 2020 |access-date=31 January 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://outbreaknewstoday.com/first-confirmed-coronavirus-case-in-spain-in-la-gomera-canary-islands-20628/ |title=First confirmed coronavirus case in Spain in La Gomera, Canary Islands |date=3 February 2020 |website=Outbreak News Today |access-date=28 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228022516/http://outbreaknewstoday.com/first-confirmed-coronavirus-case-in-spain-in-la-gomera-canary-islands-20628/ |archive-date=28 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/sanidadgob/status/1223370304275255299/photo/1 |title=El Centro Nacional de Microbiolog\u00eda ha confirmado, pasadas las diez de esta noche, que una de las muestras enviadas desde La Gomera ha dado positivo en #coronaviruspic.twitter.com/B21LojPzZD |last=Sanidad |first=Ministerio de |date=31 January 2020 |website=@sanidadgob |language=es |access-date=28 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320111846/https://twitter.com/sanidadgob/status/1223370304275255299/photo/1 |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 19 February, 2,500 soccer fans from Valencia attended a Champions League game in Bergamo, the hot spot of [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|the outbreak in Italy]].<ref name=\"guard\">{{cite news |last=Tremlett |first=Giles |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/26/spain-coronavirus-response-analysis |title=How did Spain get its coronavirus response so wrong? |date=2020-03-26 |work=The Guardian |access-date=2020-03-30 |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330000439/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/26/spain-coronavirus-response-analysis |archive-date=30 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 February, a medical doctor from [[Lombardy]], Italy who was vacationing in [[Tenerife]], tested positive at the [[Hospital Universitario Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de Candelaria|University Hospital of the Nuestra Se\u00f1ora de Candelaria]] in [[Spain]].<ref name=\":82\">{{cite web |url=https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_contagiati_in_italia-249569108/ |title=Coronavirus, positivi due italiani a Tenerife. Mille persone nell'hotel in quarantena |date=25 February 2020 |website=la Repubblica |language=it |access-date=25 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320150129/https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2020/02/25/news/coronavirus_contagiati_in_italia-249569108/ |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rtve.es/noticias/20200224/italiano-da-positivo-coronavirus-sur-tenerife/2004321.shtml |title=Un italiano da positivo por coronavirus en el sur de Tenerife |date=24 February 2020 |website=RTVE.es |language=es |access-date=27 February 2020}}</ref> Afterwards, multiple cases were detected in Tenerife involving people who had come in contact with the doctor. Other cases involving individuals who visited Italy were also discovered on Spanish mainland.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lasprovincias.es/comunitat/sanidad-confirma-nuevo-20200227090714-nt.html |title=Sanidad confirma el primer positivo por coronavirus en Valencia |date=27 February 2020 |website=Las Provincias |language=es |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227094031/https://www.lasprovincias.es/comunitat/sanidad-confirma-nuevo-20200227090714-nt.html |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn Saturday 14 March, the Spanish government imposed a nationwide quarantine, banned all trips that are not necessary and announced that companies may be intervened to guarantee supplies.<ref>[https://nationalpost.com/pmn/health-pmn/spain-to-impose-nationwide-lockdown-el-mundo Spain to impose nationwide lockdown] 14 March 2020 ''el-mundo via nationalpost.com'' accessed 16 March 2020</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://elpais.com/espana/2020-03-14/el-gobierno-prohibe-todos-los-viajes-que-no-sean-de-fuerza-mayor.html |title=El Gobierno proh\u00edbe todos los viajes que no sean de fuerza mayor |last=Cu\u00e9 |first=Carlos E. |date=2020-03-14 |website=EL PA\u00cdS |language=es |access-date=2020-03-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315040854/https://elpais.com/espana/2020-03-14/el-gobierno-prohibe-todos-los-viajes-que-no-sean-de-fuerza-mayor.html |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> However, with universities and schools closed earlier that week, bars and parks were full, and due to slow enactment \"part of the population of Madrid and other cities had dispersed across the country\".<ref name=\"guard\" />  As of 17 March 2020, there had been 11,826 confirmed cases with 1,028 recoveries and 533 deaths in Spain.<ref name=\"rtve1\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rtve.es/noticias/20200305/mapa-del-coronavirus-espana/2004681.shtml |title=El mapa del coronavirus en Espa\u00f1a |date=17 March 2020 |access-date=5 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305123308/https://www.rtve.es/noticias/20200305/mapa-del-coronavirus-espana/2004681.shtml |archive-date=5 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March, the Spanish government tightened up its national lockdown, ordering all non-essential workers to stay at home for the next two weeks.<ref>{{cite news |last=Jones |first=Sam |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/28/covid-19-may-be-peaking-in-parts-of-spain-says-official |title=Spain orders non-essential workers stay home for two weeks |date=2020-03-28 |work=The Guardian |access-date=2020-03-29 |issn=0261-3077 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329111203/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/28/covid-19-may-be-peaking-in-parts-of-spain-says-official |archive-date=29 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> Nearly 900,000 workers lost their jobs in Spain since it went into lockdown in mid-March 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/spain-coronavirus-lockdown-unemployment-job-loss-update-a9442146.html |title=Spain sees historic rise in unemployment as nearly 900,000 lose jobs since coronavirus lockdown |date=2 April 2020 |work=The Independent |access-date=3 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404013639/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/spain-coronavirus-lockdown-unemployment-job-loss-update-a9442146.html |archive-date=4 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Sweden ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Sweden}}\nOn 31 January, [[Sweden]] confirmed its first case. A woman in her 20s, who had visited Wuhan, tested positive and was admitted at Ryhov County Hospital in [[J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thelocal.se/20200131/first-case-of-coronavirus-confirmed-in-jonkoping-sweden/amp |title=First case of coronavirus confirmed in Sweden |website=thelocal.se |access-date=31 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131191731/https://www.thelocal.se/20200131/first-case-of-coronavirus-confirmed-in-jonkoping-sweden/amp |archive-date=31 January 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/nytt-bekraftat-fall-av-covid-19/ |title=Nytt bekr\u00e4ftat fall av covid-19 \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten |website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se |language=sv |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229040655/https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/nytt-bekraftat-fall-av-covid-19/ |archive-date=29 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 February, following [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|the outbreak in Italy]] and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iran|in Iran]], infection clusters originating from these two countries appeared in Sweden.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/ytterligare-fall-av-covid-19-i-flera-regioner/ |title=Ytterligare fall av covid-19 i flera regioner \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten |website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se |language=sv |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228211007/https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/ytterligare-fall-av-covid-19-i-flera-regioner/ |archive-date=28 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> A number of individuals in [[V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland County|V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland]], [[J\u00f6nk\u00f6ping]], [[Stockholm]], [[Uppsala]] tested positive and were admitted to the infectious disease units in the respective counties.<ref name=\":3\">{{cite web |url=http://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/fler-fall-upptackta-av-covid-19/ |title=Fler fall uppt\u00e4ckta av covid-19 \u2014 Folkh\u00e4lsomyndigheten |website=folkhalsomyndigheten.se |language=sv |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228210953/https://www.folkhalsomyndigheten.se/nyheter-och-press/nyhetsarkiv/2020/februari/fler-fall-upptackta-av-covid-19/ |archive-date=28 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe country's first fatality came on 11 March, that of an elderly man in Stockholm over 60 who had other illnesses prior to infection.\n\nAs of 12 March, National testing strategy shifted to only the elderly, the severely ill, and healthcare personnel. The official recommendation for symptoms that were not serious, as of 13 March, was to stay at home and not visit healthcare.  This has led to statistics becoming less useful.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.1177.se/Vastra-Gotaland/sjukdomar--besvar/infektioner/ovanliga-infektioner/covid-19-coronavirus/ |title=Covid-19 \u2013 coronavirus |date=2020-03-13 |publisher=1177 V\u00e5rdguiden |trans-title=When and where should I seek care? The vast majority of people who become ill do not need to seek care because the problems usually go away by themselves. |access-date=2020-03-15 |quote=N\u00e4r och var ska jag s\u00f6ka v\u00e5rd? De allra flesta som blir sjuka beh\u00f6ver inte s\u00f6ka v\u00e5rd eftersom besv\u00e4ren brukar g\u00e5 \u00f6ver av sig sj\u00e4lv. |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314125959/https://www.1177.se/Vastra-Gotaland/sjukdomar--besvar/infektioner/ovanliga-infektioner/covid-19-coronavirus/ |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAs of 14 March, 924 people were reported as having become infected. The [[Ministry for Foreign Affairs (Sweden)|Ministry for Foreign Affairs of Sweden]] made the [[Travel warning|recommendation to refrain from unnecessary travel]] to all countries.\n\n=== Switzerland ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Switzerland}}\nOn 25 February, following [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|the outbreak in Italy]], [[Switzerland]] confirmed its first case, a 70-year-old man in the Italian-speaking [[canton of Ticino]], who had previously visited Milan.<ref name=\"Switzerland_de2\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.blick.ch/news/coronavirus-erster-bestaetigter-fall-von-coronavirus-in-der-schweiz-id15767285.html |title=Erster best\u00e4tigter Fall in der Schweiz |date=25 February 2020 |publisher=[[Blick]] |language=de |access-date=25 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227232503/https://www.blick.ch/news/coronavirus-erster-bestaetigter-fall-von-coronavirus-in-der-schweiz-id15767285.html |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Switzerland_Ticinto\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.thelocal.ch/20200225/breaking |title=BREAKING: Switzerland confirms first case of coronavirus |date=25 February 2020 |publisher=[[The Local]] |access-date=25 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227141321/https://www.thelocal.ch/20200225/breaking |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Afterwards, multiple cases related to the Italy clusters were discovered in multiple cantons including Basel-City, Z\u00fcrich and Graub\u00fcnden.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/covid-19_switzerland-confirms-second-coronavirus-case/45582788 |title=Coronavirus cases spreading in Switzerland |website=SWI swissinfo.ch |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227084453/https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/politics/covid-19_switzerland-confirms-second-coronavirus-case/45582788 |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.gr.ch/DE/institutionen/verwaltung/djsg/ga/coronavirus/Seiten/Info.aspx |title=Informationen zum Coronavirus |website=gr.ch |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227101110/https://www.gr.ch/DE/institutionen/verwaltung/djsg/ga/coronavirus/Seiten/Info.aspx |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-swiss-idUSKCN20L167 |title=Swiss coronavirus cases rise to nine as children placed in precautionary quarantine |date=27 February 2020 |work=Reuters |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228072103/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-swiss-idUSKCN20L167 |archive-date=28 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Multiple isolated cases not related to the Italian clusters were also confirmed.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/google-employee-zurich-office-tests-191438904.html |title=Google employee who was at Zurich office tests positive for coronavirus |website=finance.yahoo.com |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200228193637/https://finance.yahoo.com/news/google-employee-zurich-office-tests-191438904.html |archive-date=28 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 28 February, the Federal Council announced an immediate ban on all events with more than 1,000 participants.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://lenews.ch/2018/03/18/geneva-international-motor-show-visitor-numbers-down-in-2018/ |title=Geneva International Motor Show visitor numbers down in 2018 |date=18 March 2018 |website=Le News |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229035649/https://lenews.ch/2018/03/18/geneva-international-motor-show-visitor-numbers-down-in-2018/ |archive-date=29 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAs of 10 March, there were 500 confirmed cases in Switzerland.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/covid-19_coronavirus--the-situation-in-switzerland/45592192 |title=Coronavirus: the situation in Switzerland |date=10 March 2020 |url-status=live |publisher=[[Swissinfo.ch]] |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307100437/https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/covid-19_coronavirus--the-situation-in-switzerland/45592192 |archive-date=7 March 2020 }}</ref>\nOn 16 March 2020, the Federal Council announced<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fnuTzODXLvw 16.03.2020 \u2013 Medienkonferenz des BR \u2013 Coronavirus (COVID-19): Aktueller Stand und Entscheide] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318111106/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fnuTzODXLvw |date=18 March 2020 }} 16 March 2020 ''www.youtube.com'', accessed 19 March 2020</ref> further measures, and a revised ordinance.<ref name=\"Bag_Ch\">[https://www.bag.admin.ch/dam/bag/de/dokumente/mt/k-und-i/aktuelle-ausbrueche-pandemien/2019-nCoV/covid-19-verordnung-2.pdf.download.pdf/COVID-19-Verordnung-2.pdf Verordnung 2 \u00fcber Massnahmen zur Bek\u00e4mpfung des Coronavirus (COVID-19)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317231248/https://www.bag.admin.ch/dam/bag/de/dokumente/mt/k-und-i/aktuelle-ausbrueche-pandemien/2019-nCoV/covid-19-verordnung-2.pdf.download.pdf/COVID-19-Verordnung-2.pdf |date=17 March 2020 }} ''www.bag.admin.ch'', accessed 19 March 2020</ref> Measures include the closure of bars, shops and other gathering places until 19 April, but leaves open certain essentials, such as grocery stores, pharmacies, (a reduced) public transport and the postal service.<ref>[https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov/massnahmen-des-bundes.html New coronavirus: Federal government measures] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304142833/https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov/massnahmen-des-bundes.html |date=4 March 2020 }} ''www.bag.admin.ch'', accessed 19 March 2020</ref>. Those measures were prolonged until 26 April 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bag.admin.ch/bag/en/home/krankheiten/ausbrueche-epidemien-pandemien/aktuelle-ausbrueche-epidemien/novel-cov/massnahmen-des-bundes.html|title=New coronavirus: Measures, ordinance and explanations|first=Federal Office of Public Health|last=FOPH|website=www.bag.admin.ch}}</ref>.\n\n=== Turkey ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Turkey}}\n\n=== Ukraine ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Ukraine}}\n\n=== United Kingdom ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom}}\n{{update-section|date=April 2020}}\n[[File:DSC05657 (49675594013).jpg|thumb|Man in [[London]] wearing a face mask on 19 March]]\nOn 31 January, [[England]] confirmed the first two cases, both members of a family of Chinese nationals staying in a hotel in [[York]] who were taken to specialist facilities in [[Newcastle upon Tyne]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thetelegraphandargus.co.uk/news/18198651.man-believed-chinese-national-taken-hospital-falling-ill-york-hotel/ |title=Chinese national taken to hospital after falling ill at Yorkshire hotel |date=30 January 2020 |work=Telegraph & Argus |access-date=30 January 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131133426/https://www.thetelegraphandargus.co.uk/news/18198651.man-believed-chinese-national-taken-hospital-falling-ill-york-hotel/ |archive-date=31 January 2020}}</ref> Afterwards, several confirmed cases were detected across the [[United Kingdom|UK]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Boseley |first=Sarah |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/06/third-person-in-uk-confirmed-as-having-coronavirus |title=First British national to contract coronavirus had been in Singapore |date=6 February 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=26 February 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200207020202/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/feb/06/third-person-in-uk-confirmed-as-having-coronavirus |archive-date=7 February 2020 |last2=Campbell |first2=Denis |last3=Murphy |first3=Simon}}</ref><ref name=\"EveningStandard\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/world/coronavirus-news-live-covid19-europe-uk-latest-a4372836.html |title=Coronavirus news LIVE: Number of UK patients hits 16 as Northern Ireland confirms first case |date=27 February 2020 |work=standard.co.uk |access-date=27 February 2020 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227203043/https://www.standard.co.uk/news/world/coronavirus-news-live-covid19-europe-uk-latest-a4372836.html |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.itv.com/news/2020-03-01/twelve-more-people-test-positive-for-coronavirus-bringing-uk-covid-19-total-to-35/ |title=Scotland confirms first case of coronavirus bringing UK total to 36 |date=1 March 2020 |website=ITV News |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301144252/https://www.itv.com/news/2020-03-01/twelve-more-people-test-positive-for-coronavirus-bringing-uk-covid-19-total-to-35/ |archive-date=1 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\nThe UK government implemented preventive measures to curb the spread of infections which included contact tracing, isolation and testing, some of which were related to the Italy clusters.<ref name=\"BBC26Feb2020\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-51641243 |title=Hundreds of flu patients to get coronavirus tests |date=26 February 2020 |work=BBC News |access-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227000207/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-51641243 |archive-date=27 February 2020 }}</ref><ref name=\"BBC24Jan2020\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-51232163 |title=China coronavirus: UK tracing up to 2,000 Wuhan visitors |date=24 January 2020 |access-date=24 January 2020 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200124064253/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-51232163 |archive-date=24 January 2020 |publisher=BBC News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/covid-19-guidance-for-staff-in-the-transport-sector/covid-19-guidance-for-staff-in-the-transport-sector |title=COVID-19: guidance for staff in the transport sector |publisher=Government of the United Kingdom |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200220133756/https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/covid-19-guidance-for-staff-in-the-transport-sector/covid-19-guidance-for-staff-in-the-transport-sector |archive-date=20 February 2020 |access-date=15 February 2020}}</ref> The [[NHS]] set up drive-through screening centres at several hospitals to test members of the public showing symptoms.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://clch.nhs.uk/about-us/news/parsons-green-drive-through-swabbing-hub-covid-19 |title=Parsons Green drive through swabbing hub for Covid-19 |publisher=Central London Community Healthcare NHS Trust |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229015242/https://clch.nhs.uk/about-us/news/parsons-green-drive-through-swabbing-hub-covid-19 |archive-date=29 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-51678008 |title=Drive-through coronavirus tests begin in Scotland |date=28 February 2020 |work=BBC News |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229033108/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-51678008 |archive-date=29 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> This effort was later replaced with screening focused on diagnosing patients in secondary care.\n\nOn 2 March, Ministers approved the [[Department of Health and Social Care]] coronavirus action plan,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/politics/breaking-coronavirus-action-plan-agreed-21614416 |title=Coronavirus action plan agreed at emergency COBRA meeting chaired by PM |last=Smith |first=Mikey |last2=Bloom |first2=Dan |date=2020-03-02 |website=mirror |access-date=2020-03-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325063107/https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/politics/breaking-coronavirus-action-plan-agreed-21614416 |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> which sets out actions to date, future measures, cooperation between devolved political and health authorities, and the level of preparedness of the country's four National Health Services. It outlined the government's objectives to deploy phased actions to '''Contain''', '''Delay''', and '''Mitigate''' any outbreak, using '''Research''' to inform policy development.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/coronavirus-action-plan |title=Coronavirus (COVID-19) action plan |website=GOV.UK |language=en |access-date=2020-03-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304154407/https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/coronavirus-action-plan |archive-date=4 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n<!-- Herd immunity is not government policy. -->On 25 March, the UK Parliament legislated to provide the government and authorities with emergency powers to handle the 2020 coronavirus pandemic, such as the power to restrict public gatherings, order businesses to close, and the ability to detain those suspected of having the virus.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2020/7/contents/enacted/data.htm |title=Coronavirus Act 2020 |website=www.legislation.gov.uk |access-date=2020-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329003536/http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2020/7/contents/enacted/data.htm |archive-date=29 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The [[Coronavirus Act 2020]] received [[Royal Assent]] on 25 March and came into force on the same day.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://services.parliament.uk/bills/2019-21/coronavirus.html |title=Coronavirus Act 2020 \u2014 UK Parliament |website=services.parliament.uk |access-date=2020-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328140026/https://services.parliament.uk/bills/2019-21/coronavirus.html |archive-date=28 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 5 April, the [[Prime Minister of the United Kingdom]] [[Boris Johnson]] was admitted to hospital after testing positive to coronavirus 10 days earlier.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-52180223|title=Coronavirus: Boris Johnson in 'good spirits' in hospital|last=|first=|date=6 April 2020|website=BBC News|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200407060247/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-52180223|archive-date=7 April 2020|access-date=}}</ref> He was admitted into [[Intensive care unit|intensive care]] the following night, when his symptoms further worsened.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-52194875|title=Coronavirus: Boris Johnson spends night in intensive care after symptoms worsen|last=|first=|date=7 April 2020|website=BBC News|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200407032232/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-52194875|archive-date=7 April 2020|access-date=7 April 2020}}</ref> He left hospital on 12 April.<ref name=\"Mason-12Apr2020\">{{cite news |last1=Mason |first1=Rowena |title=Boris Johnson leaves hospital as he continues recovery from coronavirus |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2020/apr/12/boris-johnson-leaves-hospital-as-he-continues-recovery-from-coronavirus |accessdate=12 April 2020 |work=Guardian |date=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nAs of 13 April the total of confirmed cases was 88,621; the total of recorded hospital deaths was 11,329.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-51235105|title=Coronavirus pandemic: Tracking the global outbreak|date=13 April 2020|via=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref>\n\n=== Vatican City ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Vatican City}}\n\n==Immigrants and refugees==\nEuropean Union closed borders to non-nationals on 17th March. The next day, Greece imposed restrictions on refugees\u2019 movement within camps.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://time.com/5806577/coronavirus-refugees/|title=How Coronavirus Could Affect Refugees Stranded in Greek Camps|publisher=Time|date=25 March 2020|accessdate=15 April 2020}}</ref> Thousands of asylum seekers are living in crowded camps, and there are fears that pandemic could not be controlled under such conditions. The Greek prime minister K. Mitsotakis said that Europe should do more to help because Greece \u201ccannot resolve this crisis instantly and alone\u201d.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2020/apr/07/coronavirus-doesnt-respect-barbed-wire-concern-mounts-for-greek-camps|title='Coronavirus doesn't respect barbed wire': concern mounts for Greek camps|date=7 April 2020|website=the Guardian}}</ref> Unnamed Greek officials have stated concerns that Turkey may send infected refugees and migrants towards the islands.<ref name=cnngr>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnn.gr/news/ellada/story/214957/plirofories-pos-i-agkyra-epixeirei-na-steilei-stin-ellada-metanastes-me-koronoio|title=\u03a0\u03bb\u03b7\u03c1\u03bf\u03c6\u03bf\u03c1\u03af\u03b5\u03c2 \u03c0\u03c9\u03c2 \u03b7 \u03a4\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03ba\u03af\u03b1 \u03b5\u03c0\u03b9\u03c7\u03b5\u03b9\u03c1\u03b5\u03af \u03bd\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03af\u03bb\u03b5\u03b9 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1 \u03bc\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd\u03ac\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c2 \u03bc\u03b5 \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc|date=11 April 2020|website=CNN.gr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenationalherald.com/297466/worries-grow-turkey-will-send-covid-19-migrants-to-greek-islands-eu/|title=Worries Grow Turkey Will Send COVID-19 Migrants to Greek Islands, EU|first=T. N. H.|last=Staff|date=13 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kathimerini.gr/1073483/article/epikairothta/politikh/metanastes-me-korwnoio-prow8ei-h-agkyra-sthn-ellada|title=\u039c\u03b5\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd\u03ac\u03c3\u03c4\u03b5\u03c2 \u03bc\u03b5 \u03ba\u03bf\u03c1\u03c9\u03bd\u03bf\u03ca\u03cc \u03c0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c9\u03b8\u03b5\u03af \u03b7 \u0391\u03b3\u03ba\u03c5\u03c1\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1, \u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u0392\u03b1\u03c3\u03af\u03bb\u03b7 \u039d\u03ad\u03b4\u03bf\u03c5 &#124; Kathimerini|website=www.kathimerini.gr}}</ref> Early in April Malta and Italy closed their ports to vessels carrying asylum seekers from North Africa.<ref>[https://euobserver.com/migration/148058 \"EU unable to comment on Italy and Malta port closures\", EU Observer, April 15, 2020]</ref>\n\n== Pandemic development graphs ==\n===Daily confirmed cases and deaths by date===\nDaily confirmed cases by date\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|width=800\n|height=300\n|showValues=\n|xType=date\n|xAxisFormat=%b %e\n|x=2020/02/15, 2020/02/16, 2020/02/17, 2020/02/18, 2020/02/19, 2020/02/20, 2020/02/21, 2020/02/22, 2020/02/23, 2020/02/24, 2020/02/25, 2020/02/26, 2020/02/27, 2020/02/28, 2020/02/29, 2020/03/01, 2020/03/02, 2020/03/03, 2020/03/04, 2020/03/05, 2020/03/06, 2020/03/07, 2020/03/08, 2020/03/09, 2020/03/10, 2020/03/11, 2020/03/12, 2020/03/13, 2020/03/14, 2020/03/15, 2020/03/16, 2020/03/17, 2020/03/18, 2020/03/19, 2020/03/20, 2020/03/21, 2020/03/22, 2020/03/23, 2020/03/24, 2020/03/25, 2020/03/26, 2020/03/27, 2020/03/28, 2020/03/29, 2020/03/30, 2020/03/31, 2020/04/01, 2020/04/02, 2020/04/03, 2020/04/04, 2020/04/05, 2020/04/06, 2020/04/07, 2020/04/08, 2020/04/09, 2020/04/10, 2020/04/11, 2020/04/12, 2020/04/13, 2020/04/14, 2020/04/15, 2020/04/16, 2020/04/17\n|yAxisTitle=Total No. of cases\n|legend=Legend\n|y1= 11, 11, 11, 11, 11, 11, 11, 11, 11, 11, 13, 18, 38, 57, 100, 130, 191, 212, 285, 423, 613, 949, 1126, 1412, 1784, 2281, 2876, 3661, 4499, 5423, 6633, 7730, 9134, 10995, 12612, 14459, 16018, 19856, 22302, 25233, 29155, 32964, 37575, 40174, 44550, 52128, 56989, 59105, 64338, 68605, 70478, 74390, 78167, 82048, 86334, 90676, 93790, 95403, 98076, 103573, 106206, 108847, 109252\n|y1Title=France\n|y2= 3, 3, 3, 3, 3, 3, 19, 79, 150, 227, 320, 445, 650, 888, 1128, 1694, 2036, 2502, 3089, 3858, 4636, 5883, 7375, 9172, 10149, 12462, 15113, 17660, 21157, 24747, 27980, 31506, 35713, 41035, 47021, 53578, 59138, 63927, 69176, 74386, 80539, 86498, 92472, 97689, 101739, 105792, 110574, 115242, 119827, 124632, 128948, 132547, 135586, 139422, 143626, 147577, 152271, 156363, 159516, 162488, 165155, 168941, 172434\n|y2Title=Italy\n|y3= 3, 3, 3, 3, 3, 3, 3, 3, 3, 5, 8, 14, 26, 45, 59, 84, 125, 169, 228, 282, 365, 430, 674, 1231, 1695, 2277, 3146, 5232, 6332, 7844, 9942, 11178