ova]]\n|2,351\n|60\n|391\n|\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|GRC}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Greece|Greece]]\n|2,235\n|110\n|269\n|<ref name=\"greececases\" />\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|HUN}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Hungary|Hungary]]\n|1,834\n|172\n|231\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://koronavirus.gov.hu/ |title=T\u00e1j\u00e9koztat\u00f3 oldal a koronav\u00edrusr\u00f3l |date=25 March 2020 |publisher=Cabinet Office of the Prime Minister |language=hu |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317001549/https://koronavirus.gov.hu/ |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|Croatia}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Croatia|Croatia]]\n|1,832\n|39\n|615\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.koronavirus.hr/en |title=Official government website for accurate and verified information on Coronavirus |publisher=Government of the Republic of Croatia |access-date=27 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326135722/https://www.koronavirus.hr/en |archive-date=26 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|ISL}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iceland|Iceland]]\n|1,760\n|9\n|1,291\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.covid.is/data |title=covid.is/data |last=Ss |date=2 April 2020 |website=Mbl |language=En |access-date=3 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403102907/https://www.covid.is/data |archive-date=3 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flagdeco|EST}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Estonia|Estonia]]\n|1,512\n|38\n|162\n|<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.err.ee/1064218/koroonaviirusesse-on-eestis-nakatunud-135-inimest |title=Koroonaviirusesse on Eestis nakatunud 135 inimest |publisher=ERR |language=Estonian |trans-title=135 people have already been diagnosed with coronavirus in Estonia |access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"terviseamet\">{{cite web |url=https://www.terviseamet.ee/et/uuskoroonaviirus |title=Koroonaviiruse haigus COVID-19 &#124; Terviseamet |publisher=Terviseamet.ee |